A~%3Atext%3DHow%2520fast%2520do%2520elementary%2520particles%2Cwidely%2520in%2520physics%252C%2520is%2520incomplete.%5C%22%3Ewitnessed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20similar%20phenomenon%2020%20years%20earlier%2C%20in%202001%2C%20but%20this%20unusual%20behavior%20has%20remained%20unexplained%2C%20puzzling%20physicists%20for%20over%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuons%20are%20similar%20to%20electrons%20%E2%80%94%20the%20tiny%20particles%20that%20zip%20around%20atomic%20nuclei%20%E2%80%94%20but%20are%20200%20times%20more%20massive%3B%20hence%20their%20nickname%2C%20%26quot%3Bfat%20electrons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20fat%20electrons%20can%20penetrate%20objects%20like%20X-rays%2C%20Aylin%20Woodward%20reported%20for%20Insider%2C%20and%20have%20been%20used%20to%20help%20scientists%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-corridor-great-pyramid-egypt-giza-cosmic-rays-scientists-2023-3%5C%22%3Euncover%20a%20hidden%20chamber%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Egypt's%20Great%20Pyramid%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmuons-help-map-magma-inside-volcanoes-predict-eruptions-2021-11%5C%22%3Epeer%20inside%20the%20guts%20of%20volcanoes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20they%20may%20help%20physicists%20unlock%20a%20new%20force%20of%20nature.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20an%20atomic%20nucleus%20surrounded%20by%20electrons.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64daa1a85e5d5a00195de670%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22776%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAtoms%20are%20made%20up%20of%20a%20nucleus%20of%20protons%20and%20neutrons%20surrounded%20by%20a%20cloud%20of%20electrons.%3Cp%3Eullstein%20bild%20Dtl.%20%2F%20Contributor%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLike%20electrons%2C%20muons%20have%20a%20tiny%20internal%20magnet%20that%2C%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20magnetic%20field%2C%20precesses%20or%20wobbles%20like%20the%20axis%20of%20a%20spinning%20top%2C%26quot%3B%20Fermilab%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.fnal.gov%2F2023%2F08%2Fmuon-g-2-doubles-down-with-latest-measurement%2F%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20study%20these%20muons%2C%20physicists%20fired%20them%20into%20a%20superconducting%20magnetic%20ring%20and%20measured%20how%20they%20behaved%20as%20they%20raced%20around%20thousands%20of%20times%20at%20close%20to%20the%20speed%20of%20light.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20physicists%20observed%20was%20that%20the%20muons%20were%20wobbling%20far%20more%20than%20could%20be%20predicted%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Fscience%2Fdoe-explainsthe-standard-model-particle-physics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStandard%20Model%20of%20Particle%20Physics%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mathematical%20guide%20that%20physicists%20have%20used%20for%20the%20last%2050%20years%20to%20explain%20and%20understand%20the%20subatomic%20realm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%205th%20force%20of%20nature%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22quantum%20fabric%20spacetime%20einstein%20rosen%20bridge%20wormhole%20worm%20hole%20space%20shutterstock_309841256%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5880f0eaee14b61b008b8d32%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20an%20Einstein-Rosen%20bridge%2C%20or%20wormhole%20in%20the%20fabric%20of%20space.%3Cp%3EShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20equations%20set%20down%20by%20the%20Standard%20Model%20can't%20explain%20the%20muon's%20unusual%20wobble%2C%20physicists%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20look%20for%20other%20explanations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20possible%20explanation%20is%20that%20the%20muons'%20behavior%20is%20dictated%20by%20a%20fifth%20force%20of%20nature.%20Others%20could%20be%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20new%20exotic%20particle%2C%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20new%20dimension%2C%20or%20another%20unknown%20space-time%20property%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fphysics-mathematics%2Fwobbling-muon-experiment-could-reveal-a-5th-force-of-nature-if-the-results-hold-up%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiveScience%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20really%20probing%20new%20territory%2C%26quot%3B%20Brendan%20Casey%2C%20a%20senior%20physicist%20at%20Fermilab%20said%20in%20the%20lab's%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20determining%20the%20muon%20magnetic%20moment%20at%20a%20better%20precision%20than%20it%20has%20ever%20been%20seen%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20there%20are%20two%20ways%20to%20use%20the%20Standard%20Model%20to%20describe%20the%20muon's%20wobble%2C%20and%20they%20offer%20conflicting%20results%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fphysics-mathematics%2Fwobbling-muon-experiment-could-reveal-a-5th-force-of-nature-if-the-results-hold-up%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiveScience%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20scientists%20hope%20to%20resolve%20the%20discrepancy%20is%20with%20more%20precise%20measurements.%20That's%20why%20Fermilab%20physicists%20collected%20four%20times%20more%20data%20this%20time%20compared%20to%202021%2C%20enabling%20them%20to%20reduce%20experimental%20uncertainty%20by%20a%20factor%20of%20two%2C%20LiveScience%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20expect%20another%20factor%20of%20two%20in%20precision%20when%20we%20finish%26quot%3B%20analyzing%20the%20final%20three%20years%20of%20data%2C%20said%20Graziano%20Venanzoni%2C%20the%20co-spokesperson%20of%20the%20Muon%20g-2%20experiment%20at%20Fermilab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20results%20reveal%20a%20fifth%20force%20of%20nature%2C%20it%20could%20help%20explain%20some%20of%20science's%20