er%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-indictment-georgia-court-document-rico-charges-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecounty's%20courts%20website%20momentarily%20posted%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Flegal%2Fus-state-georgia-appears-set-file-charges-against-donald-trump-court-document-2023-08-14%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eand%20then%20removed%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20document%20that%20appeared%20to%20show%20Trump%20would%20face%20charges%20including%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-georgia-investigation-fani-willis-rico-charges-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eracketeering%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E.%20%3C%2Fu%3ENicholas%20Cotten%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Fulton%20County%20courts%20system%2C%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Ba%20fictitious%20document%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-indictment-georgia-court-document-rico-charges-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWillis%20opened%20the%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20Trump%20asked%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Brad%20Raffensperger%20to%20%26quot%3Bfind%2011%2C780%20votes%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20votes%20of%20the%202020%20election%20were%20being%20tallied.%20In%202022%2C%20a%20Georgia%20special%20grand%20jury%20heard%20from%20dozens%20of%20witnesses%20including%20local%20officials%20and%20Trump%20aides%20who%20offered%20testimony%20about%20Trump's%20efforts%20to%20overturn%20the%20election%20in%20Georgia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20potentially%20faces%20a%20laundry%20list%20of%20criminal%20charges%20including%20forgery%2C%20influencing%20witnesses%2C%20election%20fraud%2C%20and%20violating%20the%20RICO%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20RICO%20Act%20is%20a%20federal%20law%2C%20Georgia%20has%20additional%20racketeering%20statutes%20that%20can%20and%20have%20been%20used%20against%20figures%20outside%20of%20mob%20bosses%20or%20typical%20criminal%20enterprises%20since%20they%20were%20adopted%20in%201980.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelissa%20Redmon%2C%20a%20director%20for%20the%20University%20of%20Georgia%20School%20of%20Law's%20Prosecutorial%20Justice%20Program%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20seeking%20the%20state's%20RICO%20Act%20would%20allow%20prosecutors%20to%20pursue%20a%20%26quot%3Bbroad%26quot%3B%20case%20involving%20multiple%20people%20and%20events%20that%20could%20have%20occurred%20at%20different%20periods%20of%20time%20and%20even%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20behind%20the%20RICO%20is%20that%20you%20can%20charge%20the%20mastermind%20with%20everything%20that%20those%20involved%20in%20the%20enterprise%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20Redmon%20said.%20And%20the%20RICO%20Act%20could%20give%20prosecutors%20the%20opportunity%20to%20give%20a%20%26quot%3Bfuller%20picture%20of%20everything%20that%20was%20done%20to%20influence%20or%20to%20disrupt%20the%20election%20in%20Georgia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20RICO%20Act%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20RICO%20Act%20was%20introduced%20by%20the%20federal%20government%20in%201970%2C%20originally%20as%20a%20legal%20means%20to%20prosecute%20mafias%20and%20entire%20groups%20involved%20in%20organized%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20law%20doesn't%20refer%20to%20a%20specific%20offense.%20Racketeering%20activity%20can%20cover%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20criminal%20activities%2C%20including%20gambling%2C%20extortion%2C%20arson%2C%20robbery%2C%20bribery%2C%20theft%2C%20and%20fraud.%20It%20is%20not%20limited%20to%20financial%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20federal%20RICO%20charge%20can%20only%20be%20brought%20when%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Farchives%2Fjm%2Fcriminal-resource-manual-109-rico-charges%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20or%20more%20of%20these%20acts%20of%20crime%20are%20committed%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20a%20span%20of%2010%20years%2C%20establishing%20a%20%26quot%3Bpattern%20of%20racketeering%20activity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20decade%20after%20the%20RICO%20Act%20was%20established%2C%20Georgia%20introduced%20its%20own%20set%20of%20statutes%20to%20go%20with%20the%20federal%20law.%20State%20lawmakers%20hoped%20to%20address%20the%20%26quot%3Bincreasing%20sophistication%20of%20various%20criminal%20elements%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ajc.com%2Fnews%2Fcrime--law%2Fgeorgia-rico-law-its-origin-and-operation%2FqyMOMjaZUadUeWuOLHkyRL%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20The%20Atlanta%20Journal-Constitution%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20statutes%20allow%20prosecutors%20to%20use%20the%20RICO%20Act%20with%20more%20flexibility%2C%20Redmon%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%20Georgia%2C%20the%20RICO%20Act%20can%20be%20used%20to%20charge%20one%20person%2C%20Redmon%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20a%20group%20of%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20version%20of%20the%20law%20requires%20that%20there%20be%20two%20acts%20of%20racketeering%20within%20a%2010-year%20span%20in%20order%20for%20prosecutors%20to%20bring%20the%20charges%2C%20while%20the%20Georgia%20RICO%20statute%20is%20not%20bound%20by%20the%20same%20time%20constraints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20has%20been%20charged%20with%20it%20lately%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWillis%2C%20who%20is%20a%20known%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-georgia-investigation-fani-willis-rico-charges-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efan%20of%20t