20with%20Earnest%20Will%2C%20the%20US%20launched%20the%20covert%20Operation%20Prime%20Chance%20to%20expose%20and%20prevent%20Iranian%20mine-laying%20in%20the%20Gulf.%20The%20first%20tanker%20to%20be%20escorted%20during%20Earnest%20Will%2C%20the%20SS%20Bridgeton%2C%20struck%20an%20Iranian%20mine%20on%20July%2024%2C%201987.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThere%20were%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNavalInstitute%2Fstatus%2F1582753160673734657%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclashes%20and%20confrontations%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20US%20and%20Iranian%20forces%20throughout%20Earnest%20Will%2C%20the%20biggest%20of%20them%20during%20Operation%20Praying%20Mantis%2C%20which%20the%20US%20launched%20four%20days%20after%20guided-missile%20frigate%20USS%20Samuel%20B.%20Roberts%20struck%20an%20Iranian%20mine%20on%20April%2014%2C%201988.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EOperation%20Praying%20Mantis%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foperation-praying-mantis-shows-destruction-of-potential-us-iran-war-2021-4%5C%22%3Ethe%20US's%20largest%20naval%20action%20since%20World%20War%20II%3C%2Fa%3E.%20During%20the%20hours-long%20fight%2C%20US%20forces%20sank%20the%20Iranian%20frigate%20Sahand%20and%20crippled%20the%20frigate%20Sabalan%2C%20which%20was%20intentionally%20left%20afloat%20to%20avoid%20further%20escalation.%20More%20than%2050%20IRGCN%20and%20Iranian%20Navy%20personnel%20were%20killed%2C%20while%20the%20US%20lost%20one%20SeaCobra%20helicopter%20and%20its%20two%20crew%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20navy%20Sahand%20Praying%20Mantis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6081c8644becb800190f69cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221460%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIranian%20frigate%20IS%20Sahand%20after%20being%20hit%20by%20Harpoon%20missiles%20and%20cluster%20bombs%20from%20US%20Navy%20aircraft%20on%20April%2019%2C%201988.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EA%20naval%20clash%20now%20would%20likely%20have%20a%20markedly%20different%20outcome.%20After%20all%2C%20Iran%20has%20made%20significant%20changes%20to%20its%20naval%20forces%20and%20tactics%20over%20the%20past%2035%20years%2C%20becoming%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20more%20asymmetric%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Bryan%20Clark%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Hudson%20Institute%20and%20expert%20on%20naval%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIran's%20naval%20force%20now%20consists%20of%20the%20Islamic%20Revolutionary%20Guard%20Corps%20Navy%2C%20known%20as%20the%20IRGCN%2C%20and%20the%20regular%20Iranian%20Navy%2C%20Clark%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20IRGCN%20operates%20in%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%20and%20uses%20mostly%20small%2C%20fast%20boats%20that%20are%20hard%20for%20traditional%20navies%20to%20counter%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20fast%20boats%20often%20carry%20anti-ship%20missiles%20or%20are%20set%20up%20to%20operate%20remotely%20and%20act%20as%20attack%20drones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20Iranian%20Navy%20still%20primarily%20consists%20of%20frigates%20and%20corvettes%2C%20which%20operate%20outside%20the%20Gulf%2C%20and%20is%20much%20more%20like%20other%20conventional%20navies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EFarzin%20Nadimi%2C%20a%20defense%20and%20security%20analyst%20at%20the%20Washington%20Institute%20for%20Near%20East%20Policy%2C%20also%20emphasized%20the%20differences%20in%20the%20capabilities%20and%20mission%20of%20the%20IRCGN%20and%20Iran's%20Navy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BThe%20IRGCN%20has%20transformed%20compared%20to%2035%20years%20ago%20with%20a%20vast%20organization%20and%20much%20more%20capabilities%20arrayed%20along%20the%20Iranian%20coastline%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadimi%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20Islamic%20Revolutionary%20Guard%20Corps%20speedboats%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64da67221f51cc0019692640%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22563%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIranian%20Islamic%20Revolutionary%20Guard%20Corps%20Navy%20speedboats%20during%20an%20exercise%20at%20Abu%20Musa%20Island%20in%20August.%3Cp%3EIRGC%2FWANA%2FHandout%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EWhile%20the%20IRGCN%20still%20largely%20relies%20on%20%26quot%3Blightly%20armed%20speedboat%20swarms%20firing%20rockets%20and%20machine%20guns%20at%20their%20targets%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20has%20supplemented%20that%20%26quot%3Bwith%20a%20large%20quantity%20of%20higher-quality%20speedboats%26quot%3B%20armed%20with%20short-%20to%20long-range%20anti-ship%20missiles%20and%20torpedoes%2C%20Nadimi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20IRGCN%20also%20has%20various%20drones%2C%20large%20numbers%20of%20water-borne%20improvised%20explosive%20devices%2C%20better%20missiles%20and%20artillery%2C%20and%20a%20more%20effective%20intelligence%20network%20than%20it%20did%2035%20years%20ago.%20On%20top%20of%20this%2C%20Iranian%20air%20defenses%20are%20also%20much%20better%20than%20they%20were%20in%20the%20late%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIran's%20navy%20has%20also%20improved.%20Iran%20has%20developed%20a%20%26quot%3Bhomegrown%20shipbuilding%20capability%26quot%3B%20and%20commissioned%20several%20indigenous%20frigates%20and%20missile%20boats%2C%20Nadimi%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EWhile%20Iranian%20navy%20ships%20have%20significantly%20improved%20their%20anti-ship%20and%20electronic-warfare%20capabilities%2C%20their%20air%20defenses%20have%20not%20changed%20much%20in%20the%20past%2035%20years%2C%20though%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Bworking%20on%26quot%3B%20that%2C%20Nadimi%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Iranian%20navy%20training%20has%20%26quot%3Bmore%20or%20less%20remained%20unchanged%26quot%3B%20for%20over%20the%20past%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iranian%20Navy%20ship%20Sahand%20in%20Persian%20Gulf%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63d2a21640fbb600192b90a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221320%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIranian%20Navy%20warship%20Sahand%20in%20Persian%20Gulf%20near%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20in%20April%202019.%3Cp%3EMorteza%20Nikoubazl%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIn%20sum%2C%20Nadimi%20said%2C%20Iran's%20naval%20forces%20have%20%26quot%3Bincreased%20quantity%3B%20higher%20quality%3B%20better%20communications%3B%20expanded%20organization%3B%20marginally%20better%20training%2C%20unchanged%20geographical%20advantages%2C%20except%20they%20have%20more%20underground%20fortifications%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20context%20of%20the%20current%20US%20deployment%20is%20also%20substantially%20different.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20Earnest%20Will%2C%20the%20US%20was%20intervening%20to%20help%20a%20partner%20state%20export%20oil%20amid%20the%20Iran-Iraq%20War%2C%20a%20major%20conflict%20that%20had%20raged%20for%20seven%20years%20by%20that%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3ENadimi%20said%20US%20lawmakers%20at%20the%20time%20feared%20the%20Earnest%20Will%20deployment%20could%20prolong%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.strausscenter.org%2Fstrait-of-hormuz-tanker-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETanker%20War%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20between%20Iran%20and%20Iraq%2C%20endanger%20the%20flow%20of%20oil%2C%20harm%20US%20neutrality%2C%20or%20push%20Iran%20closer%20to%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20worried%20the%20US%20was%20about%20to%20make%20the%20same%20mistake%20it%20made%20in%20Lebanon%26quot%3B%20by%20employing%20US%20forces%20%26quot%3Bon%20a%20symbolic%20mission%20without%20clear%20and%20attainable%20military%20objectives%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadimi%20said.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20those%20arguments%20resonate%20today%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marine%20amphibious%20assault%20ship%20Bataan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64da67221f51cc0019692643%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Marines%20train%20in%20close-quarters%20tactics%20aboard%20the%20amphibious%20assault%20ship%20USS%20Bataan%20while%20en%20route%20to%20the%20Middle%20East%20in%20July%202023.%3Cp%3EUS%20Marine%20Corps%2FCpl.%20Kyle%20Jia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIran's%20recent%20seizure%20of%20tankers%20is%20also%20not%20as%20provocative%20as%20attacking%20them%20would%20be.%20In%201987%2C%20Iran%20had%20two%20Silkworm%20anti-ship%20missile%20sites%20near%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz.%20As%20the%20convoy%20operation%20for%20the%20reflagged%20tankers%20was%20about%20to%20start%20in%20July%201987%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20US%20warned%20Iranians%20against%20any%20use%20of%20their%20newly%20deployed%20Silkworm%20missiles%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadimi%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20also%20considered%20the%20risk%20of%20escalation%20if%20Iran%20interpreted%20additional%20US%20forces%20in%20the%20region%20as%20hostile%20intent%20and%20acted%20accordingly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EToday%2C%20Iran%20has%20hundreds%20of%20high-quality%20missile%20launchers%20aimed%20at%20the%20Gulf.%20Whether%20Iran%20would%20use%20those%20missiles%2C%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-faces-a-huge-liability-in-countering-irans-use-of-sea-mines-2018-8%5C%22%3Elarge%20arsenal%20of%20sea%20mines%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20some%20other%20means%20to%20attack%20a%20US-guarded%20tanker%20in%20the%20Gulf%20today%20is%20still%20a%20matter%20of%20speculation%2C%20Nadimi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EDuring%20Earnest%20Will%2C%20US%20military%20personnel%20weren't%20deployed%20on%20the%20tankers%20being%20escorted%20%E2%80%94%20the%20US%20hasn't%20put%20troops%20on%20merchant%20vessels%20since%20World%20War%20II%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Nadimi%20doubted%20that%20such%20a%20deployment%20today%20would%20make%20conflict%20more%20likely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20there%20is%20a%20high%20risk%20of%20a%20clash%20between%20Iran%20and%20the%20US%2C%20and%20even%20placing%20armed%20US%20Marines%20on%20merchant%20ships%20and%20tankers%20%E2%80%94%20if%20it%20even%20happens%20%E2%80%94%20will%20not%20significantly%20increase%20that%20possibility%2C%20although%20it%20might%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20accidental%20escalation%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadimi%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20the%20situation%20in%20the%20Gulf%20region%20is%20not%20as%20dangerous%20and%20volatile%20as%20it%20was%20in%201987.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPaul%20Iddon%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20and%20columnist%20who%20writes%20about%20Middle%20East%20developments%2C%20military%20affairs%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20history.%20His%20articles%20have%20appeared%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20publications%20focused%20on%20the%20region.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foperation-praying-mantis-risks-of-us-iran-conflict-persian-gulf-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692050581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64da6ed51f51cc0019692eb1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foperation-praying-mantis-risks-of-us-iran-conflict-persian-gulf-2023-8%22%2C%22summary