n%20the%20Eastern%20District%20of%20Michigan%20Northern%20Division%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.mied.371487%2Fgov.uscourts.mied.371487.13.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20lawsuit%20seeking%20to%20block%20%2439%20billion%20in%20debt%20relief%20for%20800%2C000%20borrowers%20lacks%20standing%20and%20is%20dismissed.%20Last%20week%2C%20the%20New%20Civil%20Liberties%20Alliance%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20aimed%20at%20protecting%20constitutional%20freedoms%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-latest-lawsuit-block-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-2023-8%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22d04eac4fb5a9aa6047d94565454f8ca3%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2260%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-latest-lawsuit-block-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-2023-8%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3Efiled%20a%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20behalf%20of%20two%20conservative%20groups%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Cato%20Institute%20and%20the%20Mackinac%20Center%20for%20Public%20Policy%20%E2%80%94%20to%20block%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20plans%20to%20get%20relief%20to%20borrowers%20who%20made%20the%20required%2020%20or%2025%20payments%20on%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20announced%20the%20first%20batch%20of%20relief%20for%20borrowers%20due%20to%20a%20one-time%20account%20adjustment%20that%20determined%20the%20borrowers%20who%20completed%20their%20necessary%20payments%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-income-driven-repayment-adjustment-debt-relief-biden-2023-8%5C%22%3Ethe%20discharges%20of%20their%20loans%20began%20on%20Monday%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20groups%20who%20filed%20the%20lawsuit%20argued%20that%20as%20nonprofits%2C%20the%20relief%20would%20undermine%20their%20recruiting%20efforts%20through%20the%20Public%20Service%20Loan%20Forgiveness%20program%2C%20which%20forgives%20student%20debt%20for%20government%20and%20nonprofit%20workers%20after%20ten%20years%20of%20qualifying%20payments.%C2%A0Lundington%20wrote%20in%20his%20decision%20to%20dismiss%20the%20case%20that%20their%20claims%20surrounding%20PSLF%20were%20not%20sufficient%20to%20prove%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlaintiffs'%20presidents'%20own%20declarations%20do%20not%20suggest%20that%20any%20employee%20was%20actually%20impacted%20by%20the%20Adjustment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20declarations%20merely%20assert%20that%20Plaintiffs%20plan%20to%20recruit%20PSLF%20participants%20in%20the%20future%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20may%20be%20impacted%20by%20the%20Adjustment.%20This%20is%20far%20too%20speculative%20for%20standing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Mackinac%20Center's%20Director%20of%20Public%20Relations%20Holly%20Wetzel%20told%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20judge's%20ruling%20was%20not%20on%20the%20legality%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20actions%2C%20but%20rather%20he%20indicated%20that%20we%20were%20not%20the%20right%20parties%20to%20challenge%20those%20actions.%20We%20are%20currently%20reviewing%20our%20legal%20options.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20means%20that%20%E2%80%94%20barring%20other%20legal%20challenges%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Education%20Department%20will%20continue%20looking%20at%20borrowers'%20income-driven%20repayment%20accounts%20every%20two%20months%20to%20determine%20if%20they%20qualify%20for%20debt%20relief%2C%20and%20those%20who%20do%20not%20want%20the%20debt%20relief%20will%20have%20the%20option%20to%20opt%20out.%20Borrowers%20can%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdo-i-have-to-resume-student-loan-payments-debt-relief-2023-7%5C%22%3Eapply%20for%20the%20SAVE%20Plan%20before%20federal