A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fnri%2Fa-sikh-recruit-graduates-from-us-marine-corps-with-turban-beard%2Farticleshow%2F102733267.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fnri%2Fa-sikh-recruit-graduates-from-us-marine-corps-with-turban-beard%2Famp_articleshow%2F102733267.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fnri%2Fa-sikh-recruit-graduates-from-us-marine-corps-with-turban-beard%2Famp_articleshow%2F102733267.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20moved%20from%20California%20to%20Texas%20for%20a%20better%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20more%20conservative%20politics.%20Now%20I'm%20a%20realtor%20who%20helps%20others%20make%20the%20same%20move.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22930%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marie%20Bailey%20stands%20with%20her%20family%20in%20front%20of%20her%20home%20in%20Prosper%2C%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d6b46b1f51cc0019683ef3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22658%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMarie%20Bailey%20and%20her%20family%20moved%20to%20Prosper%2C%20Texas%20in%202017%2C%20where%20she%20is%20now%20a%20realtor%20helping%20other%20Californians%20make%20the%20move%20to%20The%20Lone%20Star%20State.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Marie%20Bailey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMarie%20Bailey%20moved%20from%20California%20to%20Texas%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20daughter%20in%202017.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20realtor%20said%20she%20and%20her%20family%20were%20seeking%20affordability%20and%20a%20friendlier%20place%20for%20conservatives.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBailey%20said%20she%20loves%20her%20new%20life%20in%20Texas%20and%20now%20helps%20others%20make%20the%20same%20move.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Marie%20Bailey%2C%2044%2C%20about%20her%20experience%20moving%20her%20family%20from%20El%20Segundo%2C%20California%2C%20to%20Prosper%2C%20Texas%2C%20in%202017.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20Fullerton%20in%20Orange%20County.%20I%20lived%20there%20from%20the%20time%20I%20was%20one%20until%2023.%20Then%20I%20jumped%20around%20a%20little%20bit%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20Orange%20County.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20my%20husband%2017%20years%20ago%20and%20I%20moved%20in%20with%20him%20in%20Seal%20Beach%2C%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20went%20on%20our%20first%20date%20together%2C%20we%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BOne%20day%20we're%20going%20to%20leave%20California.%26quot%3B%20We%20knew%20even%20on%20our%20first%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20lucky%20to%20be%20homeowners.%20My%20husband%20owned%20the%20house%20before%20we%20got%20married.%20Then%20his%20job%20transferred%20him.%20So%2C%20we%20rented%20it%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20rented%20in%20El%20Segundo%20so%20he%20could%20commute.%20It%20was%20just%20very%20expensive.%20You%20had%20to%20be%20working%20all%20the%20time%20to%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20rented%20in%20El%20Segundo%2C%20it%20was%20%244%2C500%20a%20month.%20Our%20electricity%20bill%20was%20quite%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20just%20felt%20like%20we%20were%20working%20constantly%20to%20afford%20a%20life%20in%20California.%20It%20always%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20never%20going%20to%20get%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20didn't%20want%20to%20pay%20that%20rent%20forever%2C%20so%20we%20were%20looking%20at%20how%20much%20houses%20cost%20in%20El%20Segundo.%20For%20a%20tiny%2C%20tiny%20fixer-upper%20at%20that%20time%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20a%20million%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20said%20this%20is%20the%20time%20we%20really%20need%20to%20start%20thinking%20about%20living%20out%20of%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20exact%20same%20time%2C%20Trump%20won%20the%20election%20in%202016.%20I'm%20not%20some%20crazy%20Trumper.%20We%20voted%20for%20him%2C%20but%20we%20aren't%20going%20to%20every%20rally%20or%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20we%20felt%20like%20we%20had%20to%20keep%20that%20a%20secret%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20After%20Trump%2C%20it%20was%20like%20we%20were%20split%20as%20a%20country.%20I%20didn't%20like%20that.%20It%20felt%20like%20we%20really%20were%20not%20welcome.%20So%2C%20I%20think%20that%20pushed%20us%20over%20the%20edge%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20took%20a%20big%20scouting%20trip%20to%20Texas%20in%202017%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20we%20figured%20out%20where%20we%20wanted%20to%20go%20and%20exactly%20how%20we%20wanted%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20other%20states%20on%20the%20list%2C%20like%20Florida%20and%20Arizona.%20But%20Texas%20has%20a%20really%20good%20travel%20hub.%20It's%20two-and-a-half%20hours%20from%20any%20coastal%20part%20of%20the%20country.%20Plus%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20tech%20jobs%20here%2C%20so%20my%20husband%20needed%20a%20place%20where%20he%20could%20get%20another%20job%20relatively%20easily%20if%20he%20needed%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20first%20started%20looking%2C%20we%20were%20looking%20at%20Frisco.%20We%20also%20looked%20at%20Rockwall%2C%20Fort%20Worth%2C%20Celina.%20Then%20we%20looked%20at%20Prosper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20growing%20suburb%20about%2045%20minutes%20outside%20of%20Dallas.%20There's%2034%2C000%20people%20here.%20%3Cem%3E%5BEditor's%20note%3A%20The%202020%20US%20Census%20lists%20Prosper%2C%20Texas%2C%20as%20having%20a%20population%20of%2030%2C167%20as%20of%20April%201%2C%202020.%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20know%20a%20lot%20about%20it%2C%20but%20what%20really%20attracted%20me%20is%20they%20have%20these%20communities%20out%20here%20that%20have%20a%20ton%20of%20amenities.%20I%20really%20wanted%20that%20community%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20neighborhood%20where%20we%20live%20now%2C%20Windsong%20Ranch%2C%20has%20a%20whole%20calendar%20of%20events.%20They%20have%20two%20pools%2C%20a%20gym%2C%20and%20a%20cafe.%20People%20are%20out%20in%20their%20golf%20carts%20all%20the%20time.%20I%20really%20liked%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20chose%20Prosper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEverybody%20was%20freaking%20me%20out%20back%20in%20California%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20come%20back%20in%20a%20year.%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20you're%20going%20to%20make%20it%20out%20there.%26quot%3B%20Not%20about%20finances%2C%20but%20because%20we%20didn't%20know%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20was%20very%20specific%20in%20choosing%20a%20neighborhood%20where%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20social%20things%20going%20on.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20isolated.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20move%20back%20because%20we%20didn't%20have%20any%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20scary%20to%20leave.%20We%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20stuff.%20Packing%20it%20all%20and%20getting%20your%20whole%20life%20together%20is%20very%20stressful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20I%20did%20it%2C%20it%20wasn't%20as%20scary%20as%20I%20thought%20it%20would%20have%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20rented%20first.%20Then%20we%20very%20quickly%20ended%20up%20choosing%20to%20build%20a%20brand%20new%20house%20in%20our%20neighborhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20time%2C%20we%20had%20to%20have%20tenants%20in%20our%20home%20in%20Seal%20Beach.%20Then%20we%20put%20that%20tiny%20house%20on%20the%20market.%20It%20wasn't%20on%20the%20beach.%20It%20wasn't%20updated%20at%20all.%20I%20think%20it%20was%20built%20in%20the%20'60s.%20We%20sold%20that%20for%20about%20the%20same%20price%20that%20we%20closed%20on%20our%20brand-new%20house%20here%20in%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20house%20is%205%2C000%20square%20feet%2C%20five%20bedrooms%2C%20has%20a%20movie%20room%2C%20a%20game%20room%2C%20two%20offices.%20It's%20on%20a%20quarter-acre%20lot.%20I%20believe%20we%20closed%20at%20about%20%24850%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20start%20to%20build%20in%20this%20community%2C%20they%20let%20you%20use%20the%20amenities.%20So%20we%20started%20to%20meet%20so%20many%20people%20just%20like%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221290%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marie%20Bailey%20and%20her%20family%20stand%20in%20front%20of%20the%20plot%20of%20land%20where%20they%20built%20their%20Texas%20house.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d6d9251f51cc0019684329%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22695%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBailey%20and%20her%20family%20were%20able%20to%20build%20their%20dream%20home%20in%20Texas%20for%20about%20the%20same%20price%20they%20sold%20their%20California%20house%2C%20she%20said.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Marie%20Bailey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20decided%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20real%20estate%20agent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20after%20we%20moved%20here%2C%20I%20got%20laid%20off%20from%20my%20job%20in%20international%20education.%20Immediately%20I%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BOkay.%20I'm%20going%20to%20be%20a%20real%20estate%20agent.%20I'm%20going%20to%20specialize%20in%20Californians%20moving%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20did.%20I%20started%20working%20on%20my%20license.%20I%20decided%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20my%20niche.%20We%20lived%20through%20the%20ins%20and%20outs%20of%20moving%20here%2C%20so%20we%20can%20help%20people%20through%20this%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20ton%20of%20people%20relocating%20here%20from%20New%20York%2C%20Chicago%2C%20and%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20created%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fgroups%2FMovetotexas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook%20group.%3C%2Fa%3E%20People%20started%20joining%20and%20now%20it%20has%20almost%2045%2C000%20members.%20It's%20a%20very%20acti