t%20Savita%20Subramanian%20issued%20a%20double%20upgrade%20to%20the%20consumer%20discretionary%20sector%20to%20overweight%20from%20underweight%2C%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%20downgrading%20the%20safer%20consumer%20staples%20sector%20to%20underweight%20from%20marketweight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20stocks%20in%20the%20consumer%20discretionary%20sector%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Famzn-stock%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Ftsla-stock%5C%22%3ETesla%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fhd-stock%5C%22%3EHome%20Depot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20the%20top%20stocks%20in%20the%20consumer%20staples%20sector%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fpg-stock%5C%22%3EProcter%20%26amp%3B%20Gamble%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fpep-stock%5C%22%3EPepsiCo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fcost-stock%5C%22%3ECostco%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubramanian's%20bullish%20upgrade%20of%20the%20riskier%20consumer%20cyclical%20sector%20was%20driven%20by%20a%20number%20of%20factors%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-recession-start-2023-bank-of-america-forecasts-2023-8%5C%22%3Ethe%20expectation%20of%20no%20US%20recession%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-economy-outlook-bullish-resilience-thesis-consumers-five-questions-2023-8%5C%22%3Esolid%20foundation%20for%20consumer%20finances%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20current%20investor%20positioning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20seven%20reasons%20why%20Subramanian%20is%20getting%20more%20bullish%20on%20the%20consumer%20discretionary%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E1.%20%26quot%3BRecession%2C%20schmecession%3A%20BofA%20expects%20a%20soft%20landing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20economists%20recently%20revised%20their%20outlook%20in%20favor%20of%20a%20soft%20landing%2C%20where%20growth%20falls%20below%20trend%20in%202024%20but%20remains%20positive.%20Their%20revised%20forecast%20is%20based%20on%20further%20evidence%20of%20continued%20resilience%20in%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20including%20positive%20GDP%20revisions%2C%20strength%20in%20business%20spending%2C%20and%20a%20rebound%20in%20labor%20supply%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20bullish%20outlook%20should%20favor%20a%20more%20risk-on%20environment%20for%20the%20consumer%20discretionary%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E2.%20Positioning%20in%20discretionary%20is%20at%20all-time%20lows.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20economists%20forecast%20a%20soft%20landing%2C%20but%20investors%20appear%20positioned%20for%20a%20GFC-style%20recession.%20Active%20funds'%20relative%20weight%20in%20Consumer%20Discretionary%20is%20at%20all-time%20lows%20in%20our%20data%20history%20for%20both%20long-only%20funds%20and%20hedge%20funds.%20Meanwhile%2C%20funds%20have%20added%20exposure%20to%20Staples%20since%202021%2C%20with%20hedge%20fund%20positioning%20near%206%2B%20year%20highs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E3.%20Flirting%20with%20early%20cycle.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20US%20Regime%20Indicator%20is%20a%20four-phase%20framework%20based%20on%20the%20amalgamation%20of%20various%20uncorrelated%20macro%20inputs.%20When%20aggregated%2C%20the%20indicator%20defines%20four%20distinct%20phases...%20After%20six%20months%20in%20the%20Downturn%20phase%2C%20our%20indicator%20moved%20higher%20in%20July%2C%20signaling%20a%20potential%20new%20phase%20%E2%80%93%20Early%20Cycle.%20We%20wait%20for%20a%20second%20month%20of%20confirmation%20of%20a%20new%20regime%20before%20considering%20this%20an%20official%20shift%20to%20the%20Early%20Cycle%20phase...%20Consumer%20Discretionary%20has%20typically%20outperformed%20in%20Early%20Cycle%2C%20while%20Consumer%20Staples%20tends%20to%20lag.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22837%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Early%20cycle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64da70ca1f51cc001969314b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22711%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBank%20of%20America%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3E4.%20Discretionary%20earnings%20delivered%20a%20big%20beat%20in%202nd%20quarter.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDiscretionary%20is%20tracking%20the%20biggest%20top%2Fbottom%20line%20beat%20so%20far%20this%20earnings%20season%20(%2B3%25%2C%20%2B20%25%20respectively).%20Consensus%20estimates%20for%20Discretionary%20have%20finally%20started%20to%20catch%20up%20to%20Staples%2C%20pointing%20to%20a%20better%20consumer%20outlook.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E5.%20%26quot%3BHomebuilders%20are%20the%20canary%20in%20the%20coal%20mine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHousing%20has%20shown%20signs%20of%20nearing%20a%20bottom%2C%20and%20homebuilders%20troughed%20late%20last%20year.%20This%20supports%20Consumer%20Discretionary%20as%20the%20sector%20most%20correlated%20with%20housing%20data.%20Discretionary%20leadership%20typically%20follows%20Homebuilders.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E6.%20Real%20wage%20growth%20back%20to%20positive.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReal%20wage%20growth%20is%20positive%20again%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20two%20years.%20Discretionary%20has%20historically%20been%20the%20biggest%20beneficiary%20(along%20with%20Tech)%20of%20real%20wage%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E7.%20Negative%20consumer%20headlines%20are%20overblown.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBurning%20through%20excess%20savings%20sounds%20bad.%20And%20the%20consumer%20has%20remained%20resilient%20despite%20inflation%2C%20as%20excess%20savings%20from%20pandemic-era%20stimulus%20allowed%20for%20an%20extended%20period%20of%20low%20saving%20rates%20but%20no%20strain%20on%20con