2%80%99s%20first%20lunar%20lander%20mission%20in%2047%20years.%20It%20could%20even%20be%20viewed%20as%20the%20first%20Russian%20mission%20to%20the%20moon%20since%20all%20the%20earlier%20missions%20were%20undertaken%20during%20the%20Soviet%20era.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Russian%20space%20agency%20Roscosmos%2C%20Luna%2025%20is%20likely%20to%20reach%20the%20moon%20in%20five%20days%20and%20remain%20in%20the%20lunar%20orbit%20for%20five%20to%20seven%20days%20before%20attempting%20a%20soft%20landing%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface.%20The%20agency%20has%20already%20narrowed%20down%20on%20two%20or%20three%20potential%20landing%20spots%20which%20are%20close%20to%20the%20south%20pole%20of%20the%20moon.%20These%20sites%20are%20within%20a%2015-km%20wide%20and%2030-km%20long%20area.%20If%20successful%2C%20the%20mission%20will%20last%20for%20one%20year%20and%20involve%20undertaking%20various%20observations%20and%20scientific%20experiments.%20It%20may%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20lunar%20south%20pole%20is%20a%20big%20area%20and%20none%20of%20these%20landing%20zones%20are%20%E2%80%98dissecting%E2%80%99%20the%20proposed%20landing%20site%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fchandrayaan-3-mission-launch-successful%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20mission%E2%80%99s%20Luna-Glob-Lander%20weighs%20around%20800%20kg%20(plus%20950%20kg%20of%20fuel)%2C%20and%20has%20four%20legs%20with%20landing%20rockets%2C%20fuel%20tanks%20and%20solar%20panels.%20It%20has%20been%20designed%20to%20study%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20moon%E2%80%99s%20south%20polar%20soil%2C%20the%20plasma%20and%20dust%20present%20in%20the%20very%20thin%20lunar%20exosphere.%20As%20per%20reports%2C%20Luna%2025%E2%80%99s%20lander%20(there%20is%20no%20rover%20unit%20like%20Chandrayaan-3)%20has%20a%20robotic%20arm%2C%20which%20can%20move%20in%20different%20directions%20and%20is%20equipped%20with%20a%20scoop%20to%20collect%20lunar%20samples.%20There%20are%20various%20other%20instruments%20to%20study%20the%20samples%20and%20the%20lunar%20exosphere.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20robotic%20arm%20has%20a%20tool%20(4.7%20cm-long%20tube)%20and%20scooper%20to%20hold%20nearly%20175%20cubic%20cm%20of%20material.%20The%20lander%20has%20eight%20scientific%20tools%20to%20collect%20data%20and%20undertake%20experimentation.%20Broadly%2C%20assessments%20like%20measuring%20the%20gamma%20rays%20and%20neutrons%20coming%20from%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20moon%2C%20measuring%20water%20content%20on%20the%20moon%E2%80%99s%20surface%2C%20and%20studying%20the%20composition%20and%20thermal%20proteins%20of%20the%20regolith%20(lunar%20dust)%20would%20be%20undertaken.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20India%20embarked%20on%20its%20quest%20for%20the%20moon%20with%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20Chandrayaan-1%20in%202008%2C%20Russia%20(as%20the%20erstwhile%20Soviet%20Union)%20is%20an%20old%20player.%20The%20Luna%20Program%E2%80%99s%20first%20mission%20was%20in%201959.%20Subsequently%2C%2024%20other%20missions%20were%20carried%20out%20until%201976%20%E2%80%93%20including%20some%20failures.%20All%20these%20missions%20had%20different%20goals%3A%20flyby%20missions%2C%20missions%20involving%20the%20craft%20orbiting%20the%20moon%20and%20some%20soft%20landings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20news%20reports%20have%20noted%20that%20though%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20mission%20was%20launched%20after%20India%2C%20it%20is%20expected%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbeat%E2%80%9D%20the%20Chandrayaan%20mission%20by%20reaching%20the%20lunar%20surface%20faster.%20It%20needs%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20had%20already%20accomplished%20many%20%E2%80%98firsts%E2%80%99%20in%20this%20domain.%20They%20were%20the%20first%20to%20undertake%20a%20flyby%20mission%20of%20the%20moon%2C%20to%20have%20a%20lunar%20satellite%20and%20to%20have%20an%20impact%20(drop%20equipment%20to%20reach%20the%20lunar%20surface)%20on%20the%20moon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInterestingly%2C%20during%20the%20Chandrayaan-1%20mission%20on%20November%2014%2C%202008%2C%20India%20also%20dropped%20the%20Moon%20Impact%20Probe%20on%20the%20moon%E2%80%99s%20surface.%20India%20became%20the%20first%20country%20to%20do%20this%20on%20the%20south%20pole%20of%20the%20moon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Soviets%20were%20also%20the%20first%20to%20take%20photographs%20of%20the%20far%20side%20of%20the%20moon.%20They%20also%20achieved%20the%20first%20lunar%20soft%20landing%2C%20deployed%20a%20lunar%20rover%20and%20undertook%20an%20analysis%20of%20lunar%20soil.%20In%20addition%2C%20they%20also%20brought%20back%20the%20first%20lunar%20sample%20to%20the%20Earth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApart%20from%20the%20Luna%20Program%2C%20the%20Soviets%20also%20had%20a%20program%20called%20Zond%2C%20which%20looked%20at%20the%20moon%2C%20Mars%2C%20and%20Venus.%20This%20robotic%20spacecraft%20programme%20(1964-1970)%20had%20two%20spacecraft%20series%2C%20one%20for%20interplanetary%20exploration%2C%20and%20the%20other%20for%20lunar%20exploration.%20One%20very%20interesting%20aspect%20of%20this%20programme%20was%20that%20during%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spacecentre.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fspace-now-blog%2Fzond-5-tortoises-at-the-moon%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520mission%2520would%2520last%2520for%2Cas%2520they%2520are%2520sometimes%2520known.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EZond%205%20mission%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20first%20terrestrial%20organisms%20%E2%80%93%20two%20tortoises%20and%20some%20other%20lifeforms%20%E2%80%93%20survived%20their%20journey%20around%20the%20moon%20in%20a%20capsule%20and%20returned%20to%20Earth.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20Cold%20War%20period%2C%20the%20Soviets%20and%20the%20US%20competed%20for%20superior%20space%20technology.%20The%20Soviets%20demonstrated%20their%20capability%20by%20becoming%20the%20first%20nation%20to%20send%20a%20satellite%20to%20space%20(Sputnik%2C%201957)%2C%20and%20the%20first%20human%20to%20space%20(Yuri%20Gagarin%2C%201957).%20However%2C%20they%20were%20defeated%20by%20the%20US%20in%20manned%20lunar%20missions%20(starting%20with%20Apollo%2011%20in%201969).%20Unfortunately%2C%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20(or%20Russia)%20was%20not%20able%20to%20undertake%20a%20human%20mission%20to%20the%20moon.%20Their%20human%20lunar%20programme%20was%20kept%20secret%20and%20details%20of%20it%20were%20made%20public%20only%20in%201990.%20The%20Zond%20programme%20had%20some%20focus%20on%20developing%20a%20human%20lunar%20programme.%20In%20addition%2C%20from%201969%20to%201972%2C%20they%20undertook%20four%20tests%20(all%20unsuccessful)%20of%20the%20N1%2FL3%20rocket%2C%20a%20super%20heavy-lift%20launch%20vehicle%2C%20possibly%20the%20Soviet%20counterpart%20to%20the%20US%20Saturn%20V%2C%20which%20was%20used%20for%20the%20manner%20moon%20mission.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20by%20naming%20its%20mission%20to%20the%20moon%20%E2%80%9CLuna%2025%E2%80%9D%2C%20Russia%20is%20clearly%20demonstrating%20that%20it%20wants%20to%20carry%20forward%20the%20Soviet%20space%20legacy.%20Russia%20understands%20that%20its%20cosiness%20with%20the%20US%20in%20the%20domain%20of%20space%20%E2%80%93%20which%20began%20post-Cold%20War%20with%20collaboration%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS)%20%E2%80%93%20has%20no%20future%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Frussia-war-ukraine-damage-international-spaceflight-cooperation%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eowing%20to%20the%20Ukraine%20crisis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20In%202021%2C%20Russia%20and%20China%20unveiled%20their%20roadmap%20to%20send%20humans%20to%20the%20moon%20by%20building%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fchina-russia-international-lunar-research-station%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EInternational%20Lunar%20Research%20Station%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%2021st-century%20space%20race%2C%20the%20Russians%20are%20late%20starters%20and%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20match%20the%20ambitions%20of%20the%20US%20or%20China%20in%20taking%20humans%20to%20the%20moon.%20However%2C%20Russia%20could%20try%20to%20regain%20some%20of%20its%20past%20glory%20by%20collaborating%20with%20friendly%20nations%20like%20China%20and%20Iran.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAjey%20Lele%20researches%20space%20issues%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%3C%2Fem%3EInstitutions%20That%20Shaped%20Modern%20India%3A%20ISRO%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692024343000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F04122047%2Fsatellite-67718_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Frussia-moon-agenda-luna-25%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Luna%2025%20is%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20lunar%20lander%20mission%20in%2047%20years.%20It%20could%20even%20be%20viewed%20as%20the%20first%20Russian%20mission%20to%20the%20moon%20since%20all%20the%20earlier%20missions%20were%20undertaken%20during%20the%20Soviet%20era.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Frussia-moon-agenda-luna-25%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%5C%22Citizens%20Equal%2C%20Have%20Equal%20Rights%5C%22%3A%20President's%20Independence%20Day%20Message%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPresident%20of%20India%20Droupadi%20Murmu%2C%20addressing%20the%20nation%20on%20the%20eve%20of%2077th%20Independence%20Day%2C%20said%20she%20wants%20the%20daughters%20of%20India%20%26quot%3Bto%20move%20forward%26quot%3B%20and%20be%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Bface%20every%20challenge%26quot%3B.%20She%20also%20underscored%20the%20right%20to%20equality%20granted%20by%20the%20Constitution%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BEach%20Indian%20is%20an%20equal%20citizen%2C%20each%20one%20has%20equal%20opportunity%2C%20rights%20and%20duties%20in%20this%20land%26quot%3B.%20Their%20identities%20as%20Indian%20citizens%20over-rides%20all%20other%20identities%20of%20caste%2C%20creed%20and%20language%2C%20she%20said%20in%20her%20second%20speech%20as%20President%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Murmu%20said%20women%20are%20now%20participating%20in%20every%20sphere%20for%20India's%20development%2C%20taking%20on%20responsibilities%20that%20were%20not%20thought%20of%20a%20few%20decades%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20women%20are%20contributing%20extensively%20in%20every%20field%20of%20development%20and%20service%20to%20the%20country%20and%20are%20enhancing%20the%20nation's%20pride.%20Today%20our%20women%20have%20made%20their%20special%20place%20in%20many%20such%20fields%20in%20which%20their%20participation%20was%20unimaginable%20a%20few%20decades%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20happy%20to%20note%20that%20the%20economic%20empowerment%20of%20women%20is%20being%20given%20special%20focus%20in%20our%20country.%20Economic%20empowerment%20strengthens%20the%20position%20of%20women%20in%20the%20family%20and%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20President%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20the%20daughters%20of%20the%20country%20to%20move%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20citing%20examples%20of%20leaders%20like%20Sarojini%20Naidu%2C%20Ammu%20Swaminathan%2C%20Rama%20Devi%2C%20Aruna%20Asaf-Ali%20and%20Sucheta%20Kriplani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaa%20Kasturba%20matched%20the%20Father%20of%20the%20Nation%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20every%20step%20of%20the%20way%20on%20the%20difficult%20path%20of%20Satyagraha%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnPresident%20Murmu%20said%20India%20has%20not%20only%20regained%20its%20%26quot%3Brightful%20place%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20world%20stage%20but%20it%20has%20also%20enhanced%20its%20standing%20in%20the%20world%20order.%20This%20is%20evident%20from%20the%20new%20confidence%20in%20the%20India%20story%20exuded%20by%20the%20expat%20Indians%20which%20she%20has%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndia%20is%20playing%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20promoting%20developmental%20and%20humanitarian%20goals%20around%20the%20world.%20It%20has%20also%20assumed%20leadership%20of%20international%20forums%2C%20especially%20the%20presidency%20of%20G-20%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20President%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20notable%20in%20India's%20presidency%20of%20the%20G20%20is%20the%20way%20this%20diplomatic%20activity%20has%20been%20taken%20to%20the%20grassroots.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20campaign%20to%20encourage%20people's%20participation...all%20the%20citizens%20are%20enthusiastic%20about%20events%20related%20to%20the%20G20%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20there%20were%20many%20global%20issues%20that%20concern%20all%20humanity%20and%20are%20not%20limited%20by%20geographical%20boundaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20confident%20that%20with%20India's%20proven%20leadership%20in%20dealing%20with%20global%20issues%2C%20member-nations%20will%20be%20able%20to%20advance%20effective%20action%20on%20these%20fronts%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20President%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692023880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fcu3e1178_droupadi-murmu-650_650x400_14_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwant-indian-women-to-be-able-to-face-every-challenge-president-droupadi-murmu-4297521%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20of%20India%20Droupadi%20Murmu%2C%20addressing%20the%20nation%20on%20the%20eve%20of%2077th%20Independence%20Day%2C%20said%20she%20wants%20the%20daughters%20of%20Ind