20it%20misleading%3F%20And%20if%20the%20boast%20is%20unwarranted%2C%20does%20that%20raise%20serious%20questions%20about%20the%20Production%20Linked%20Incentive%20(PLI)%20scheme%3F%20Is%20it%20a%20success%3F%20Or%20could%20it%20be%20responsible%20for%20funnelling%20wasteful%20expenditure%20or%20at%20least%20money%20that%20could%20be%20better%20spent%3F%20Joining%20me%20to%20answer%20those%20questions%20live%20from%20Chicago%20is%20the%20former%20governor%20of%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20and%20now%20professor%20of%20finance%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%2C%20Raghuram%20Rajan.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDr%20Rajan%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20claims%20that%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20India%20has%20become%20a%20major%20manufacturer%20of%20mobile%20phones.%20As%20proof%2C%20they%20claim%20that%20between%202017-18%20and%202022-2023%2C%20net%20exports%20have%20grown%20from%20-3.3%20billion%20to%209.8%20billion%2C%20which%20is%20a%20turnaround%20of%2013.1%20billion.%20However%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20raised%20serious%20questions%20about%20this%20claim%2C%20and%20I%20want%20to%20go%20through%20them%20one%20by%20one.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirst%2C%20you%20say%20it%20turns%20out%20that%20very%20little%20apart%20from%20assembly%20is%20done%20in%20India.%20In%20fact%2C%20industry%20experts%20have%20told%20you%20that%20mobile%20companies%20have%20imported%20completely%20knocked-down%20kits%20and%20then%20assembled%20phones%20in%20India.%20Now%20this%20is%20critical.%20Are%20you%20certain%20of%20this%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20thanks%20Karen%20for%20having%20me.%20And%20let%20me%20set%20the%20context%20a%20little%20bit.%20This%20is%20about%20more%20than%20just%20a%20scheme%20of%20the%20government.%20The%20reality%20is%2C%20jobs%20matter%20hugely%20in%20India.%20And%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20job%20situation%2C%20manufacturing%20jobs%20have%20stayed%20relatively%20flat%20as%20a%20fraction%20of%20overall%20jobs%20for%20the%20last%20three%20decades%20or%20so.%20And%20so%20most%20developing%20countries%20develop%20by%20creating%20many%20more%20manufacturing%20jobs%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20China%20developed.%20And%20so%2C%20there%20is%20this%20feeling%20that%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20create%20manufacturing%20jobs%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20sort%20of%20falling%20behind.%20And%20the%20truth%20is%2C%20there%20are%20areas%20where%20we%20have%20very%20strong%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%93%20two-wheelers%20for%20example%2C%20auto%20ancillaries%2C%20pharmaceuticals.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20by%20and%20large%2C%20we%20seem%20to%20have%20missed%20the%20manufacturing%20bus.%20And%20therefore%20the%20government%20is%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9COh%20well%2C%20we%20need%20to%20increase%20manufacturing%2C%20how%20do%20we%20do%20that%3F%E2%80%9D%20We%20have%20these%20disabilities%20%E2%80%93%20our%20infrastructure%20is%20not%20great%2C%20our%20workers%20are%20not%20as%20qualified%20as%20workers%20elsewhere%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20do%20R%26amp%3BD%20%5Bresearch%20and%20development%5D%2C%20etc.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20government-acknowledged%20disability%2C%20and%20they%20say%20we%20have%20to%20compensate%20for%20that.%20And%20then%20manufacturing%20will%20come%20to%20India.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20context%20for%20the%20PLI%20scheme.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20parts.%20One%2C%20we%20raise%20tariffs%20on%20what%20we%20want%20to%20manufacture%20in%20India%20so%20people%20can%E2%80%99t%20actually%20sort%20of%20bring%20them%20into%20the%20domestic%20market%20without%20paying%20those%20tariffs.%20That%20gives%20protection%20for%20production%20in%20India.%20But%20in%20addition%2C%20there%20is%20a%20production%20incentive.%20For%20example%2C%20for%20mobile%20phones%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%206%25%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20invoice%20price.%20The%20government%20will%20give%20that%20to%20you%20as%20a%20subsidy%20to%20compensate%20for%20all%20the%20disabilities%20of%20manufacturing%20in%20India.%20So%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20scheme.%20The%20intent%20is%20%E2%80%93%20let%E2%80%99s%20bring%20production%20to%20India.%20And%20whenever%20the%20government%20talks%20about%20this%2C%20it%20says%20manufacturing%20is%20up%2C%20exports%20are%20up.%20Now%2C%20if%20you%20are%20a%20manufacturer%20and%20you%E2%80%99re%20producing%20in%20East%20Asia%20and%20you%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9COh%2C%20the%20government%20has%20just%20erected%20tariffs%2C%20so%20I%20need%20to%20produce%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%20But%20what%20does%20production%20mean%3F%20The%20government%20cannot%20say%20you%20have%20to%20make%20this%20and%20that%20%E2%80%93%20there%E2%80%99s%20some%20loose%20definition%20of%20production.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20turns%20out%20that%20if%20they%20assemble%20the%20stuff%20in%20India%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20enough%20to%20qualify.%20And%20in%20fact%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20doing%20%E2%80%93%20they%E2%80%99re%20basically%20bringing%20all%20the%20components%20to%20India%20and%20then%20with%20the%20old%20screwdriver%20technology%2C%20putting%20it%20together%20in%20large%20factories%20and%20saying%20we%E2%80%99re%20manufacturing%20in%20India.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20if%20the%20government%20is%20giving%20you%206%25%20of%20the%20price%20to%20export%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20huge%20export%20subsidy%20%E2%80%93%20I%20might%20as%20well%20export%20from%20India%20also.%20And%20so%20overnight%2C%20because%20of%20the%20tariffs%20we%E2%80%99ve%20increased%20what%20is%20%E2%80%9Cproduced%20in%20India%E2%80%9D.%20And%20over%20time%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20also%20increased%20the%20export%20significantly%20and%20we%E2%80%99re%20now%20saying%20this%20is%20wonderful.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20is%20just%20assembly.%20Where%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20further%20sub-assemblies%2C%20but%20we%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20this.%20What%20fraction%20of%20value%20is%20that%3F%20You%20know%20somebody%20from%20the%20industry%20basically%20said%2C%20the%20entire%20%5Bplan%5D%20is%20to%20shape%20aluminium%20sheets%20into%20iPhone%20SE%20cases%2C%20drill%20the%20holes%2C%20and%20then%20export%20the%20semi-finished%20shells%20to%20China%20for%20final%20assembly.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20kind%20of%20stuff%20%E2%80%93%20where%20we%20are%20calling%20manufacturing%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing.%20We%E2%80%99re%20not%20doing%20sophisticated%20stuff%20here.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Ft4pd7BVJ5Vw%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20in%20a%20nutshell%2C%20the%20government%20ought%20to%20rephrase%20its%20boast.%20We%20are%20not%20a%20major%20%3Cem%3Emanufacturer%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20mobile%20phones%2C%20but%20we%20could%20claim%20to%20be%20a%20major%20%3Cem%3Eassembler%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20manufacturing%20phone%20parts%20which%20are%20then%20exported%20to%20another%20country%20where%20the%20actual%20phone%20is%20put%20together.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20would%20say%20more%20than%20that.%20Yes.%20We%20are%20assembling%20final%20phones%20in%20India%20also%2C%20but%20we%20are%20starting%20to%20become%20part%20of%20value%20chains%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20credit.%20But%20the%20reality%20is%2C%20for%20every%20Rs%20100%20of%20the%20invoice%20price%20of%20the%20phone%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20paying%20Rs%206%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmanufacturer%E2%80%9D%2C%20right.%20(I%20want%20to%20keep%20saying%20quote%20unquote%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20assembly%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20call%20them%20assemblers.)%20Now%2C%20think%20about%20it.%20If%20you%20look%20at%20the%20typical%20phone%2C%20say%20an%20iPhone%2C%20for%20which%20we%20have%20detailed%20data.%20But%2030%25%20of%20the%20final%20price%20is%20manufacturing.%20That%E2%80%99s%20because%20the%20rest%20of%20it%20is%20services%20like%20the%20intellectual%20property%20that%20Apple%20charges%20for%20and%20I%E2%80%99ll%20tell%20you%20something%20more%20about%20that%20in%20a%20second.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20when%20I%20look%20at%20that%20iPhone%2C%20about%204%25%20of%20the%20value%20is%20for%20assembly.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20entire%20assembly%20value.%20And%20so%20if%20the%20government%20is%20paying%20Rs%206%20for%20it%20and%20the%20cost%20is%20only%20Rs%204%2C%20why%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20anybody%20bring%20assembly%20into%20India%3F%20They%E2%80%99re%20making%20money%20on%20it%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20they%20would.%20Why%20would%20they%20do%20it%20if%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20making%20money%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%2C%20however%2C%20is%20when%20you%20look%20at%20the%20value%20added%20in%20a%20phone%2C%20or%20any%20electronics%20or%20any%20sophisticated%20manufacturing.%20Manufacturing%20over%20time%20has%20become%20less%20and%20less%20of%20the%20value%20added.%20As%20I%20said%2C%20in%20the%20iPhone%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%20Rs%2030-40%20out%20of%20100.%20The%20remaining%20is%20in%20the%20initial%20part%20%E2%80%93%20the%20intellectual%20property%2C%20and%20the%20design%20that%20goes%20into%20it%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20final%20part%20%E2%80%93%20the%20marketing%2C%20the%20finance%2C%20etc.%20That%E2%80%99s%20Rs%2060%20to%2065%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20where%20all%20the%20profits%20are.%20So%20take%20Apple.%20Apple%2C%20the%20company%2C%20is%20worth%20US%20%243%20trillion.%20Apple%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20manufacture%20anything%2C%20Foxconn%20manufactures%20for%20Apple.%20Foxconn%E2%80%99s%20market%20value%20is%20%2450%20billion.%203%20trillion%2C%2050%20billion.%20So%2C%2060%20times%20the%20value.%20What%20we%20are%20trying%20for%20is%20what%20Foxconn%20is%20doing%20%E2%80%93%20the%20lowest%20part%20of%20the%20value-added%20chain.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%20say%20this%20is%20going%20to%20produce%20low-skilled%20jobs%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20true.%20The%20question%20is%2C%20is%20it%20going%20to%20do%20any%20more%3F%20And%20we%E2%80%99re%20paying%20for%20those%20low-skill%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20focus%20a%20little%20on%20that%204%25%2C%20as%20you%20put%20it%2C%20that%20India%20is%20doing%20by%20its%20assembly.%20Because%20your%20second%20point%20takes%20your%20first%20point%20about%20assembling%20a%20good%20critical%20step%20further.%20You%20write%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20still%20Imports%20much%20of%20what%20goes%20into%20the%20mobile%20phone%2C%20and%20when%20we%20correct%20for%20that%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20hard%20to%20maintain%20that%20net%20exports%20have%20gone%20up.%E2%80%9D%20And%20then%20very%20importantly%20you%20add%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndeed%20we%20cannot%20even%20tell%20from%20the%20data%20whether%20India%20is%20paying%20out%20more%20in%20subsidies%20and%20tax%20waivers%20to%20mobile%20manufacturers%20who%20bring%20the%20assembly%20to%20India%20than%20the%20value%20they%20add%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%20That%20last%20thought%20is%20particularly%20disturbing%20because%20it%20suggests%20that%2C%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20right%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20gaining%20very%20much%2C%20if%20anything%20at%20all.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20paying%20manufacturers%20to%20bring%20work%20to%20India.%20Effectively%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20paying%20the%20wages%20of%20those%20workers.%20Now%20the%20key%20point%20is%20whether%20this%20grows%20into%20something%20much%20bigger.%20And%20the%20problem%20of%20course%20is%20with%20these%20global%20supply%20chains%2C%20especially%20for%20relatively%20small%20items%20where%20transportation%20costs%20are%20really%20low.%20You%20know%2C%20bringing%20it%20into%20India%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20you%20do%20the%20rest%20in%20India.%20You%20can%20take%20it%20out%20back%20and%20forth%20%E2%80%93%20like%20we%20talked%20about%20the%20cell%20phone%20shell.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20really%20the%20problem%2C%20that%20this%20may%20remain%20where%20it%20is%20%E2%80%93%20that%20you%20pay%20for%20this%20work%2C%20they%20do%20this%20work%20in%20India%20so%20long%20as%20you%E2%80%99re%20paying%20them%2C%20and%20then%20when%20the%20subsidies%20stop%20they%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CWell%2C%20thank%20you.%20It%20was%20nice%20being%20in%20India%2C%20but%20you%20haven%E2%80%99t%20fixed%20the%20disabilities%20that%20force%20you%20to%20pay%20the%20subsidies.%E2%80%9D%20In%20other%20words%2C%20bribing%20people%20to%20come%20to%20India%20is%20not%20useful%20if%20when%20you%20stop%20paying%20them%20they%20leave.%20So%20there%20has%20to%20be%20something%20which%20really%20keeps%20them%20in%20India%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20something%20to%20think%20about%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20government%20strategy%20%E2%80%93%20bring%20them%20in%20a%20big%20way%20and%20everything%20else%20will%20happen.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20happened%20in%20China%20but%20we%E2%80%99re%2030%20years%20or%2040%20years%20on%20from%20when%20China%20did%20this.%20And%20the%20question%20is%2C%20can%20this%20happen%20again%3F%20But%20the%20broader%20point%20the%20government%20actually%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20dispute%20our%20numbers%20%E2%80%93%20I%20will%20come%20later%20to%20this%20%E2%80%93%20but%20I%20think%20it%20sort%20of%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CHey%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20importing%2032%20billion%20precisely%20for%20PLI%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20importing%2022%20billion%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20exporting%2011.%20So%20the%20net%20imports%20is%2011%20billion.%E2%80%9D%20So%20the%20government%20is%20not%20disputing%20the%20fact%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20importing%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20content%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20the%20point%20about%20whether%20this%20can%20lead%20to%20something%20more%20and%20something%20bigger%20when%20I%20come%20to%20the%20way%20you%E2%80%99ve%20been%20criticised%20by%20Rajiv%20Chandrasekhar%2C%20because%20that%20is%20the%20basis%20of%20his%20claim%20%E2%80%93%20that%20this%20is%20only%20a%20starting%20point.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20drill%20a%20little%20further%20into%20the%20figures%20that%20you%20were%20about%20to%20recite%20because%20I%20think%20they%20really%20substantiate%20the%20point%20you%E2%80%99ve%20made.%20They%E2%80%99re%20a%20little%20complicated%20for%20lay%20audiences%2C%20so%20I%E2%80%99ll%20take%20them%20slowly.%20You%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20mobile%20phone%20exports%20really%20took%20off%20from%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202021%2C%20there%20was%20a%20commensurate%20rise%20in%20net%20inputs%20of%20imports.%20And%20when%20you%20add%20the%20combined%20imports%20of%20semiconductors%2C%20PCBAs%2C%20displays%2C%20cameras%20and%20batteries%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3Eamounted%20to%20%2432.4%20billion%20in%202023.%E2%80%9D%20And%20this%20means%2C%20and%20this%20is%20the%20critical%20thing%2C%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnet%20exports%20of%20final%20phones%2C%20and%20semiconductors%2C%20PCBAs%2C%20and%20other%20mobile%20parts%20fell%20from%20minus%2012.7%20billion%20in%202017%20to%20minus%2021.3%20billion%20in%202023%E2%80%9D.%20That%E2%80%99s%20almost%2C%20but%20not%20quite%2C%20a%20100%25%20fall.%20And%20your%20conclusion%20is%20telling%2C%20you%20say%20it%E2%80%99s%20entirely%20possible%20that%20we%20have%20become%20more%20dependent%20on%20imports%20during%20the%20PLI%20scheme.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20our%20exports%20have%20gone%20up%20%E2%80%93%20they%20have%20a%20little%2C%20But%20our%20imports%20have%20gone%20up%20much%2C%20much%20more.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20so%20exports%20have%20gone%20up%20quite%20a%20bit%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20where%20the%20government%20boasts%20from%20the%20rooftops%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20become%20a%20mobile%20phone%20exporter.%20But%20again%2C%20we%20have%20to%20understand%20what%20that%20means.%20It%20means%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20putting%20together%20the%20final%20mobile%20phone%20in%20India%2C%20importing%20all%20the%20parts%2C%20and%20then%20exporting%20a%20certain%20fragment.%20Yes%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20positive%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20exporting.%20But%20it%20does%20raise%20the%20question%2C%20are%20we%20paying%20for%20the%20exports%3F%20As%20I%20said%2C%20through%20these%20subsidies%2C%20how%20much%20are%20we%20paying%20per%20job%20that%20we%20are%20creating%3F%20And%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20more%20obscurity%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20clear%20how%20many%20additional%20jobs%20have%20been%20created%2C%20and%20what%20the%20cost%20per%20job%20is.%20But%20I%20think%20the%20point%20is%2C%20you%20know%2C%20we%20may%20have%20become%20more%20dependent%20over%20time.%20Some%20of%20that%20may%20also%20be%20that%20our%20demand%20for%20smartphones%20has%20increased%20over%20time%20and%20therefore%20we%E2%80%99re%20importing%20more.%20So%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20lay%20all%20that%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20government.%20But%20the%20broader%20point%20is%20%E2%80%93%20again%20and%20again%20%E2%80%93%20where%20are%20we%20going%20to%20go%20from%20here%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20this%20point%20about%20the%20PLI%20scheme%2C%20also%20this%20has%20become%20the%20single%20government%20scheme%20in%20manufacturing%20to%20increase%20jobs.%20Uou%20see%20PLI%20schemes%20here%2C%20PLI%20schemes%20there.%20And%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20asking%20%E2%80%93%20what%20my%20co-authors%20and%20I%20are%20asking%20%E2%80%93%20is%20do%20we%20know%20it%20works%3F%20Can%20we%20establish%20with%20the%20first%20area%20where%20we%20did%20it%2C%20which%20is%20mobile%20phones%2C%20that%20it%20actually%20creates%20many%20more%20jobs%20and%20it%20creates%20more%20jobs%20than%20we%20are%20paying%20for%3F%20And%20that%20those%20jobs%20have%20persisted%2C%20they%20will%20not%20disappear%20over%20time.%20And%20also%2C%20as%20you%20think%20about%20this%2C%20ask%20which%20areas%20are%20being%20picked%20for%20PLI%3F%20What%20is%20the%20government%20thinking%20that%20goes%20into%20picking%20say%20windmills%20or%20batteries%20for%20PLI%3F%20Is%20it%20just%20this%20is%20the%20latest%20shiny%20area%3F%20Do%20we%20have%20a%20comparative%20advantage%20so%20that%20jobs%20actually%20stick%20there%3F%20And%20will%20manufacturers%20make%20investment%20even%20if%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20pay%20them%3F%20If%20you%20do%20pay%20them%2C%20when%20they%20were%20willing%20to%20make%20investment%20you%E2%80%99re%20actually%20paying%20more%20than%20you%20should.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20have%20right%20now%20is%20this%20wonderful%20circumstance%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20manufacturers%20across%20the%20world%20are%20worried%20about%20China.%20And%20they%20are%20looking%20for%20China%2B1%20strategies.%20Maybe%20they%20come%20to%20India.%20Apple%20has%20said%20that%2C%20because%20it%20wants%20an%20alternative%20to%20China.%20Do%20you%20have%20to%20pay%20Apple%2C%20the%20richest%20company%20in%20the%20world%2C%20to%20come%20to%20India%3F%20Or%20will%20it%20just%20come%20anyway%3F%20So%20there%20are%20all%20these%20questions.%20Do%20you%20need%20to%20pay%3F%20How%20much%20are%20you%20getting%20per%20job%3F%20We%E2%80%99re%20not%20a%20rich%20country.%20There%E2%80%99s%20so%20much%20more%20we%20can%20do%20with%20that%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20finally%20%E2%80%93%20and%20this%20is%20where%20the%20scheme%20is%20%3Cem%3Eso%3C%2Fem%3E%20obscure%20%E2%80%93%20how%20did%20the%20data%20on%20how%20you%20pay%20get%20determined%3F%20You%20remember%20the%20time%20when%20we%20paid%20companies%20based%20on%20investment