uld%20actually%20have%20to%20be%20as%20low%20as%2040%25%20for%20net%20exports%20to%20become%20positive%20and%20as%20you%20say%2C%20the%20real%20number%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20much%20higher%20than%2040%25.%20So%20when%20Mr%20Chandrasekhar%2C%20half%20reading%20or%20perhaps%20half%20understanding%20your%20article%2C%20criticises%20you%20for%20assuming%20that%20all%20imports%20of%20semiconductors%2C%20PCBAs%20etc.%2C%20are%20going%20into%20mobile%20manufacturing%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20already%20answered%20it.%20Even%20if%20only%2060%25%20is%20going%20in%2C%20net%20exports%20are%20still%20negative.%20It%20has%20to%20be%20as%20low%20as%2040%2C%20which%20is%20very%20unlikely%2C%20for%20them%20to%20become%20positive.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20to%20the%20credit%20of%20the%20minister%2C%20he%20actually%20responded%2C%20which%20is%20good.%20We%20can%20talk%20about%20the%20tone%20of%20the%20response%2C%20which%20is%20not%20so%20good.%20But%20I%20think%20the%20point%20here%20is%20that%20without%20the%20data%20you%20have%20to%20make%20assumptions.%20And%20to%20call%20assumptions%20lies%2C%20I%20think%20is%20overstating%20the%20case.%20It%E2%80%99s%20basically%20saying%20it%20could%20be%20this%20or%20it%20could%20be%20that%20%E2%80%93%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20know.%20So%20we%20assume%20that%20it%20could%20be%20anywhere%20between%2040%25%20to%2080%25%20of%20the%20imports%20were%20used%20in%20the%20mobile%20phone%20sector.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20minister%20basically%20said%20it%20was%2065%25%20%E2%80%93%20that%20was%20almost%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20our%20range%2C%20but%20slightly%20higher%2C%20which%20makes%20the%20imports%20even%20higher%20than%20we%20thought%20it%20would.%20And%20essentially%2C%20yes%2C%20we%20are%20importing%20a%20lot%20of%20what%20goes%20into%20our%20exports.%20What%20you%20hear%20the%20government%20speaking%20about%2C%20including%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%3Cspan%3E%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3Ethat%20we%20have%20become%20a%20mobile%20phone%20exporter.%20But%20they%20never%20talk%20about%20the%20imports%20we%20are%20doing%20and%20that%20matters%20because%20the%20difference%20is%20in%20a%20sense%20the%20value%20we%20are%20adding%20in%20India.%20And%20so%20far%2C%20it%20has%20been%20very%20little.%20So%20a%20lot%20depends%20on%20what%20happens%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28141558%2Fravi-sharma-HCoHGXiDMpE-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28141558%2Fravi-sharma-HCoHGXiDMpE-unsplash.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28141558%2Fravi-sharma-HCoHGXiDMpE-unsplash-300x186.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28141558%2Fravi-sharma-HCoHGXiDMpE-unsplash-1024x633.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665619%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22742%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20government%20withheld%20incentives%20claimed%20by%20Samsung%20Electronics%20Co.%20Ltd%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20scheme%20totalling%20Rs%20900%20crore%20on%20the%20sales%20of%20about%20Rs%2015%2C000%20crore%2C%20citing%20invoicing%20discrepancies.%20Photo%3A%20Ravi%20Sharma%2FUnsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20for%20the%20audience%20underline%20two%20things%20you%E2%80%99ve%20established%20before%20I%20go%20further.%20One%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20mobile%20phone%20manufacturers%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20better%20described%20as%20mobile%20phone%20assemblers.%20And%20secondly%2C%20when%20the%20government%20boasts%20that%20you%E2%80%99re%20exporting%20mobile%20phones%2C%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20overlooking%20is%20the%20vast%20quantity%20of%20imports%20that%20go%20in%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20phone%20that%20we%20export%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20quite%20possible%20that%20net%20exports%20are%20negative.%20This%20leads%20you%20to%20two%20conclusions%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaran%2C%20it%20is%20not%20just%20%E2%80%9Cquite%20possible%E2%80%9D%20that%20net%20exports%20are%20negative%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is.%20The%20number%20has%20been%20confirmed%20by%20the%20minister.%20We%20are%20importing%20in%20the%20PLI%20scheme%2C%2011%20billion%20more%20than%20we%20export%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuite%20right%2C%20as%20he%20said%2065%25%20of%20the%20imports%20of%20the%20items%20I%20mentioned%20go%20into%20the%20mobile%20phone%20industry%2C%20which%20is%20way%20above%20the%20threshold%20of%2040%25%20at%20which%20net%20exports%20will%20become%20positive.%20This%20leads%20you%20in%20your%20articles%20to%20two%20conclusions%2C%20let%20me%20put%20them%20to%20you%20one%20by%20one%3A%20first%2C%20you%20say%20we%20certainly%20cannot%20claim%20the%20rise%20in%20exports%20of%20finished%20cell%20phones%20is%20evidence%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20prowess%20in%20manufacturing.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20we%20were%20assembling%20phones%20before%20the%20PLI%20scheme%20was%20started%20and%20before%20tariffs%20were%20introduced%2C%20and%20essentially%2C%20even%20after%20those%20schemes%20were%20introduced%20we%E2%80%99re%20still%20assembling%20phones.%20Effectively%2C%20as%20far%20as%20assembly%20is%20concerned%2C%20nothing%20much%20has%20changed.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20I%20mean%20again%2C%20to%20give%20the%20government%20credit%2C%20maybe%20we%E2%80%99ve%20moved%20a%20little%20more%20into%20sub-assembly%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20assembling.%20The%20reality%20really%20is%20that%20you%20know%2C%20you%20have%20to%20ask%20yourself%2C%20how%20long%20are%20we%20going%20to%20do%20this%3F%20How%20long%20will%20it%20take%20to%20move%20from%20this%20level%20to%20the%20next%20level%2C%20and%20is%20it%20going%20to%20really%20happen%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20really%20where%20the%20entire%20scheme%20is%20based%20on.%20We%20pay%20these%20guys%20for%20a%20little%20while%2C%20they%20come%20to%20India%2C%20they%20build%20scale%20and%20then%20over%20time%20magic%20happens.%20Yhey%20start%20doing%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20other%20stuff%2C%20and%20yeah%20maybe%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20hope.%20And%20I%20do%20have%20a%20hope%20that%20we%20become%20a%20manufacturing%20giant%20on%20that%20basis.%20But%20the%20reality%20is%20the%20world%20has%20changed.%20They%20will%20manufacture%20wherever%20it%E2%80%99s%20cheapest%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20China%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20gone%20away.%20China%20still%20has%20enormous%20numbers%20of%20workers%20in%20the%20Western%20provinces%20it%20wants%20to%20bring%20into%20formal%20manufacturing.%20Vietnam%20has%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20skilled%20workers.%20If%20we%20want%20to%20compete%20with%20these%20countries%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20through%20temporary%20bribes%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20compete%20with%20them.%20We%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20compete%20with%20them%20by%20improving%20the%20underlying%20%5Bsituation%5D%2C%20remedying%20the%20disabilities.%20In%20a%20sense%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20real%20question%3A%20how%20fast%20are%20we%20moving%20there%3F%20The%20single%20biggest%20disability%20we%20have%20is%20the%20quality%20of%20our%20workers.%20When%20you%20talk%20to%20manufacturers%2C%20industrialists%2C%20again%20and%20again%20they%20say%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20find%20skilled%20work%2C%20those%20that%20we%20need.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20leads%20directly%20to%20your%20second%20conclusion%20and%20that%20is%20the%20questioning%20of%20the%20PLI%20scheme.%20You%E2%80%99ve%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20already%20but%20let%20me%20put%20to%20the%20audience%20what%20you%20wrote%20in%20that%20article.%20You%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20key%20question%20is%20whether%20the%206%25%20subsidy%20India%20pays%20on%20the%20finished%20mobile%20phone%2C%20coupled%20with%20state%20subsidies%2C%20actually%20outweighs%20the%20value%20added%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%20And%20you%20then%20went%20on%20to%20ask%2C%20%E2%80%9CIs%20the%20scheme%20a%20failure%20in%20the%20making%3F%E2%80%9D%20Am%20I%20right%20in%20saying%20that%20your%20clear%20hunch%20is%20it%20is%3F%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20so%20categorical%20at%20this%20point.%20What%20I%20would%20say%20is%20we%20have%20to%20give%20the%20benefit%20of%20doubt.%20This%20is%20an%20idea%2C%20but%20so%20far%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20it%20is%20a%20scheme%20that%20works%2C%20and%20I%20think%20therefore%20the%20government%20has%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20more%20to%20look%20at%20the%20details%20of%20the%20scheme%20and%20to%20convince%20itself%20that%20this%20is%20worth%20spreading%20to%20every%20other%20sector.%20But%20what%20you%20see%20is%20without%20doing%20that%20evaluation%2C%20without%20being%20confident%20of%20its%20success%20%E2%80%93%20just%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20statements%20like%20we%E2%80%99ve%20become%20a%20mobile%20phone%20exporter%20%E2%80%93%20we%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20it%20extended%20to%20sector%20after%20sector.%20And%20there%20is%20absolutely%20no%20discussion%20in%20the%20public%20as%20to%20how%20these%20sectors%20are%20chosen.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20should%20I%20subsidise%20this%20rather%20than%20that%3F%20And%20remember%2C%20these%20subsidies%20don%E2%80%99t%20go%20to%20every%20manufacturer%20in%20the%20sector%20%E2%80%93%20they%20go%20to%20a%20chosen%20few.%20How%20are%20those%20few%20chosen%3F%20Does%20it%20make%20sense%20to%20privilege%20the%20bigger%20manufacturers%20in%20that%20sector%3F%20Some%20of%20them%20are%20foreign%20manufacturers%20%E2%80%93%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20against%20that.%20All%20I%E2%80%99m%20saying%20is%2C%20how%20do%20we%20know%20how%20the%20government%20is%20doing%20all%20this%3F%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20huge%20contingent%20liability%20we%E2%80%99re%20building%20up.%20On%20what%20basis%3F%20And%20the%20government%20is%20not%20transparent%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20know%20you%20began%20that%20answer%2C%20Dr%20Rajan%2C%20by%20saying%20I%E2%80%99m%20prepared%20for%20now%20to%20give%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt%20to%20the%20government%2C%20and%20that%20to%20me%20sort%20of%20fingers%20crossed%20situation.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20data%20but%20let%E2%80%99s%20hope%20it%20works%20out%20right.%20But%20this%20then%20raises%20the%20critical%20question%3A%20is%20the%20money%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20spending%20on%20the%20PLI%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20small%20penny%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20%E2%80%93%20could%20it%20be%20better%20spent%20otherwise%3F%20You%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CSpending%20on%20PLI%20means%20not%20spending%20on%20something%20else.%E2%80%9D%20You%20say%20%E2%80%9Cgovernment%20can%20instead%20spend%20money%20on%20creating%20high%20quality%20schools%20and%20universities%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20you%20critically%20add%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdeveloping%20and%20expanding%20the%20education%20sector%20would%20be%20a%20large%20industry%20in%20itself%20with%20large%20externalities%20which%20would%20generate%20for%20the%20economy%20and%20for%20society%E2%80%9D.%20So%20clearly%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20hint%20there%2C%20if%20not%20something%20stronger%2C%20that%20the%20money%20spent%20on%20PLI%20%E2%80%93%20if%20your%20hope%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20materialise%20%E2%80%93%20is%20money%20that%E2%80%99s%20wasted%20or%20at%20least%20money%20that%20could%20have%20been%20and%20should%20have%20been%20better%20spent.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20start%20asking%20whether%2C%20the%20fact%20we%20haven%E2%80%99t%20grown%20in%20manufacturing%20is%20something%20we%20should%20take%20for%20granted%20and%20not%20keep%20saying%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20become%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20manufacturer.%20But%20look%20at%20the%20area%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20creating%20jobs.%20So%20manufacturing%2C%20the%20ILO%20says%2C%20from%202012%20to%202021%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20moved%20from%2097%20million%20jobs%20to%20100%20million%20jobs%20%E2%80%93%20%5Bthat%E2%80%99s%5D%203%20million%20jobs%20%5Bcreated%2C%20which%5D%20is%20peanuts.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20service%20sector%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20moved%20by%20about%2020%20million%20jobs.%20Now%2C%20these%20are%20formal%20jobs.%20The%20point%20is%20there%20is%2C%20there%20is%20an%20area%20we%20are%20more%20successful%20%E2%80%93%20much%20more%20successful%2C%20and%20that%20is%20in%20creating%20service%20jobs.%20We%20are%20so%20fixated%20on%20getting%20chip%20manufacturing%20to%20India.%20Chip%20manufacturing%20again%2C%20is%20the%20final%20production%20stage.%20What%20we%20are%20really%20good%20at%20is%20chip%20design.%20We%20have%2C%20through%20the%20back%20offices%20of%20some%20of%20these%20big%20firms%20%E2%80%93%2020%25%20by%20one%20estimation%20%E2%80%93%20of%20chip%20design%20in%20the%20world.%20So%20are%20you%20going%20to%20hanker%20about%20bringing%20chip%20manufacturing%20to%20India%2C%20or%20are%20you%20going%20to%20expand%20the%20chip%20design%3F%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20how%20do%20you%20get%20chip%20design%3F%20Not%20by%20building%20foundries%20%E2%80%93%20which%20are%20the%20most%20expensive%20part%20of%20chips%2C%20the%20foundry%20that%20Intel%20is%20building%20costs%20%2420%20billion.%20It%20is%20by%20creating%20minds%2C%20by%20creating%20engineers%2C%20who%20are%20going%20to%20do%20that%20chip%20design.%20And%20that%20means%20upgrading%20the%20quality%20of%20our%20engineering%20output.%20I%20work%20with%20a%20university%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20looking%20for%20a%20spectrometer%20so%20that%20the%20kids%20can%20do%20research%20in%20chemistry%2C%20the%20faculty%20can%20do%20research%20in%20chemistry.%20It%20costs%20Rs%2018%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20a%20secondhand%20spectrometer%20costs%20Rs%2018%20crore.%20And%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20being%20able%20to%20do%20it%20for%20want%20of%20that%20input.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20train%20minds.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20build%20gold-plated%20capital%20in%20this%20country.%20If%20we%20train%20those%20minds%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20see%20a%20huge%20expansion%20in%20service%20exports.%20In%20fact%2C%20over%20the%20last%20three%20years%20since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20as%20we%E2%80%99ve%20got%20services%20at%20a%20distance%2C%20the%20area%20that%20is%20succeeding%20is%20not%20in%20manufacturing.%20In%20fact%2C%20manufacturing%20exports%20are%20sort%20of%20dead%20in%20the%20water.%20What%E2%80%99s%20really%20taking%20off%20is%20services%20exports.%20Even%20that%20is%20slowing%20down%20now%20because%20of%20a%20slow%20down%20in%20the%20West.%20But%20what%20has%20really%20helped%20us%20is%20service%20exports.%20So%2C%20instead%20of%20hankering%20to%20be%20like%20China%2C%20why%20don%E2%80%99t%20we%20be%20like%20India%3F%20Focus%20on%20the%20service%20sector.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20they%20say%20our%20service%20sector%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20produce%20low-quality%20jobs%20which%20we%20need%20for%20the%20large%20level%20of%20moderately%20skilled%20people%20who%20are%20coming%20out%20of%20agriculture.%20But%20it%20does!%20The%20biggest%20job%20in%20India%20is%20security%20guard.%20Then%20we%20have%20jobs%20like%20retail.%20Then%20we%20have%20jobs%20like%20tourism.%20All%20of%20them%20employ%20in%20services.%20People%20of%20moderate%20skills.%20So%2C%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20if%20we%E2%80%99re%20focusing%20on%20exports%20let%E2%80%99s%20capture%20the%20biggest%20part%20of%20the%20value%20chain.%20Richard%20Baldwin%20calls%20this%20a%20smile.%20The%20intellectual%20property%20in%20the%20early%20part%2C%20the%20marketing%20and%20finance%20in%20the%20later%20part.%20That%E2%80%99s%20where%20the%20value%20added%20is.%20That%E2%80%99s%20where%20we%20have%20the%20capability%2C%20a%20highly%20trained%20human%20capital%20to%20capture%20that.%20Why%20are%20we%20looking%20for%20the%20lowest%20part%20of%20the%20value%20chain%3F%20Why%20do%20we%20want%20to%20be%20slaves%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20by%20picking%20up%20low-skilled%20manufacturing%2C%20even%20if%20it%20contributed%20to%20higher-skill%20manufacturing%2C%20which%20I%20said%20is%20not%20at%20all%20clear%20nowadays%2C%20because%20companies%20just%20produce%20wherever%20it%E2%80%99s%20most%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20last%20point.%20TSMC%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20%5Blargest%5D%20manufacturer%20of%20chips%2C%20is%20worth%20%24450%20billion.%20Nvidia%2C%20which%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20manufacture%20a%20single%20chip%2C%20just%20designs%20it%2C%20is%20worth%20%241%20trillion.%20And%20add%20to%20that%20Qualcomm%2C%20Broadcomm.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20go%20into%20chip%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%93%20we%20already%20have%20a%20large%20presence%20there.%20Focus%20on%20your%20strengths%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20focus%20on%20the%20weaknesses%20because%20you%20have%20no%20imagination.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEverything%20that%20you%20said%20raises%20critical%20questions%20about%20the%20agreement%20that%20we%20reached%20in%20June%20when%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20visited%20the%20United%20States%20with%20Micron%20to%20manufacture%20ships%20in%20India.%20And%20you%20address%20that%20directly%20in%20your%20article.%20You%20say%20if%20after%20five%20years%20of%20tariffs%20plus%20PLI%20in%20mobile%20phones%2C%20India%20makes%20few%20of%20even%20the%20simplest%20parts%2C%20should%20we%20really%20be%20investing%20in%20the%20Micron%20plant%3F%20And%20before%20you%20answer%20that%2C%20remember%2070%25%20of%20the%20%242.75%20billion%20investment%20is%20coming%20not%20from%20Micron%20but%20from%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20and%20the%20Union%20government.%20Micron%20is%20only%20putting%20in%2030%25%2C%20is%20putting%20in%20roughly%20%24750%20million%20in%20India.%20Its%20investments%20in%20America%20run%20into%20billions%20of%20dollars.%20Literally%20two%20or%20three%20hundred%20billions%20of%20dollars%2C%20so%20what%E2%80%99s%20the%20answer%20to%20your%20question%3F%20Is%20this%20a%20wise%20move%20or%20a%20mistake%3F%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20simply%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20it%20and%20maybe%20the%20minister%20or%20others%20in%20government%20understand%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20here.%20Micron%20says%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20is%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20bring%20assembly%20and%20testing%20of%20chips%20to%20India.%20So%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20as%20if%20we%E2%80%99ll%20become%20independent.%20We%E2%80%99ll%20still%20be%20importing%20the%20wafers%2C%20the%20etching%20all%20that%20will%20be%20done%20elsewhere%20and%20maybe%20we%20cut%20it%20up.%20But%20what%20are%20we%20getting%3F%20We%E2%80%99re%20getting%205%2C000%20jobs.%20We%20are%20paying%20%242%20billion%20for%205%2C000%20jobs.%20That%E2%80%99s%20Rs%203.2%20crore%20per%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20you%20know%20%5Bpeople%20ask%5D%2C%20why%20not%20do%20it%3F%20Well%2C%20we%20have%20limited%20resources.%20So%20%242%20billion%20is%20something%20like%20Rs%2016%2C500%20crore.%20The%20entire%20higher%20education%20budget%2C%20which%20produces%20all%20those%20IIT%20engineers%20who%20are%20creating%20such%20a%20wave%20in%20services%2C%20the%20entire%20higher%20education%20budget%20of%20the%20government%20is%20Rs%2044%2C000%20crore.%20You%E2%80%99re%20spending%20more%20than%20one-third%20of%20the%20budget%2C%20the%20higher%20education%20budget%2C%20on%20subsidising%20a%20rich%20semiconductor%20firm%20to%20bring%20some%20of%20its%20production%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%E2%80%99re%20not%20going%20to%20become%20independent%3B%20we%20will%20still%20import%20chips%2C%20we%20will%20still%20import%20the%20parts%20for%20the%20chips%20from%20elsewhere.%20Why%3F%20What%20is%20the%20logic%20behind%20this%20other%20than%20we%E2%80%99ve%20got%20a%20shiny%20factory%20in%20India%20and%20we%20can%20claim%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20chip%20manufacturing%3F%20I%20mean%20why%20do%20we%20need%20chip%20manufacturing%20at%20this%20point%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20entire%E2%80%A6%20and%20by%20the%20way%20these%20are%20not%20logic%20chips%2C%20these%20are%20memory%20chips.%20Logic%20chips%20which%20is%20where%20the%20heart%20of%20chip%20manufacturing%20is%20requires%20a%20much%20bigger%20investment.%20That%E2%80%99s%20where%20we%20were%20talking%20about%20the%20%2410%20billion%20%5Bjoint%20venture%20by%5D%20Foxconn%20and%20Vedanta.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20what%20those%20guys%20have%20what%2C%20you%20know%2C%20abilities%20they%20have%20in%20manufacturing%20chips%20which%20leads%20to%20the%20question%20again%2C%20how%20are%20we%20choosing%20these%20guys%3F%20That%20was%20the%20big%20sort%20of%20chip%20venture%20till%20those%20guys%20decided%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20going%20to%20do%20it.%20So%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20non-transparency%20in%20this%20whole%20process.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20want%20to%20come%20at%20this%20point%20to%20the%20criticism%E2%80%99s%20made%20of%20your%20analysis%20by%20Rajiv%20Chandrasekhar%2C%20the%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Electronics%2C%20but%20I%20will%20underline%20for%20the%20audience%20one%20critical%20thing%20you%20say%3A%20the%20Micron%20project%2C%20if%20it%20happens%20will%20be%20creating%205000%20jobs%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%203.2%20crore%20a%20job.%20It%E2%80%99s%20almost%20an%20unimaginable%20figure%2C%20and%20yet%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20truth.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOkay.%20Against%20that%20background%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20come%20to%20Rajiv%20Chandrasekhar%E2%80%99s%20criticisms.%20And%20again%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20go%20through%20several%20of%20them%20one%20by%20one.%20First%2C%20he%20says%2C%20your%20conclusion%20is%20not%20rocket%20science.%20He%20says%20without%20question%20all%20electronics%20manufacturing%20begins%20with%20assembly%2C%20which%20is%20light%20on%20value%20addition.%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20says%20all%20complex%20manufacturing%20across%20all%20sectors%20usually%20begins%20with%20assembly.%20But%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20as%20the%20component%20and%20sub-assembly%20ecosystem%20builds%20up%2C%20driven%20by%20scale%20and%20supported%20by%20exports%2C%20new%20jobs%20are%20created%2C%20value%20addition%20increases%20and%20domestic%20companies%20join%20the%20global%20supply%20chain.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20what%20he%E2%80%99s%20saying%20is%20this%20is%20how%20electronics%20manufacturing%20has%20to%20begin%2C%20and%20you%20are%20either%20ignorant%20of%20that%20or%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20it.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20he%20has%20his%20opinion.%20The%20reality%20is%20global%20supply%20chains%20used%20to%20be%20when%20transportation%20costs%20were%20high%2C%20sort%20of%20get%20aggregated%20around%20where%20you%20are%20doing%20most%20of%20the%20production.%20What%20used%20to%20happen%20was%20in%20Asia%20was%20what%20was%20called%20the%20Flying%20Geese%2C%20that%20you%20start%20with%20low%20skill%20manufacturing%2C%20and%20then%20others%20ahead%20of%20you%20in%20the%20value%20chain%20give%20up%20because%20their%20workers%20have%20become%20more%20expensive%20and%20you%20move%20up%20the%20scale.%20The%20problem%20is%20we%E2%80%99re%20starting%20after%20China.%20We%E2%80%99re%20starting%20when%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20competitors%20like%20Vietnam.%20And%20so%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20vacating%20those%20parts%20in%20the%20higher%20skill%20part%20of%20the%20supply%20chain%2C%20and%20they%20have%20these%20skilled%20workers%20to%20do%20that%20kind%20of%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20this%20notion%20that%20somehow%20you%20start%20with%20low-skilled%20assembly%20%E2%80%93%20in%20fact%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20buying%20low-skilled%20assembly%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20even%20that%20you%E2%80%99re%20more%20competent%20at%20it%20%E2%80%93%20but%20somehow%20we%E2%80%99ll%20migrate%20up%2C%20you%20have%20to%20tell%20me%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20doing%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20will%20happen.%20If%20you%E2%80%99re%20investing%20tremendously%20in%20creating%20higher-skilled%20workers%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20entirely%20with%20you.%20The%20opportunity%20for%20moving%20up%20is%20there.%20If%20all%20you%E2%80%99re%20doing%20is%20paying%20people%20to%20come%20here%20and%20assemble%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20not%20investing%20in%20the%20next%20step%2C%20which%20is%20creating%20the%20conditions%20to%20move%20up%20the%20value%20chain.%20And%20that%20is%20not%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20do.%20It%E2%80%99s%20what%20the%20government%20has%20to%20do%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20anything%20here%20which%20says%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20that.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20mean%20in%20some%20sense%2C%20the%20problem%20is%20we%E2%80%99ve%20been%20assembling%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20We%20were%20assembling%20computers%20since%20the%201980s.%20Remember%20when%20there%20was%20liberalisation%2C%20and%20we%20started%20being%20able%20to%20buy%20HCL%20Busybee%20computers%20and%20so%20on%3F%20We%E2%80%99ve%20been%20assembling%20cell%20phones.%20There%20was%20a%20Nokia%20plant%20which%20got%20closed%20down%20in%202012-13.%20We%20were%20assembling%20mobile%20phones%20there.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20been%20done%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20Where%20are%20we%20moving%20up%20the%20next%20step%3F%20So%2C%20if%20you%20think%20about%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20good%20at%20manufacturing%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20in%20the%20commodity%20manufacturing.%20It%E2%80%99s%20where%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ci%3Ejugaad%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3Ea%20lot%20of%20value%20added%20based%20on%20small%20improvements%20in%20technology%2C%20small%20improvements%20in%20reliability%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20your%20two-wheeler%20manufacturing%20or%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20pharmaceuticals%2C%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20you%20know%20the%20%3Ci%3Ejugaad%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%20in%20trying%20to%20get%20other%20processes%20by%20which%20we%20can%20make%20generics.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%E2%80%99re%20not%20great%20at%20fundamental%20research%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20great%20at%20commodity%20manufacturing.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20I%20keep%20asking%2C%20how%20are%20we%20picking%20these%20sectors%3F%20Do%20we%20know%20we%20have%20any%20advantage%20there%3F%20Or%20are%20we%20just%20saying%20China%20does%20it%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20do%20it%3F%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20worst%20reason%20to%20do%20it%20because%20China%E2%80%99s%20there%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20going%20to%20move.%20And%20you%20know%20people%20will%20do%20China%2B1%20but%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20going%20to%20move%20a%20lot%20to%20India%20unless%20you%20fix%20the%20problems.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20the%20sake%20of%20the%20audience%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20point%20out%20that%20Mr%20Chandrasekhar%20simply%20asserts%20in%20his%20response%20to%20you%20that%20we%20will%20move%20to%20the%20next%20step.%20He%20assumes%20it%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20but%20he%20has%20no%20evidence%20for%20it%20and%20no%20reason%20to%20either%20believe%20that%20this%20will%20happen%20now.%20He%20then%20goes%20on%20to%20actually%20criticise%20you%20for%20things%20you%20haven%E2%80%99t%20said.%20I%