-massacre-rights-group-calls-for-international-probe%2Fa-45066244%5C%22%3EOther%20rights%20organisations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0have%C2%A0described%20it%20as%20one%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Frabaa-riots-darkest-day-in-egyptian-modern-history%2Fa-18647298%5C%22%3Eworst%20mass%20killings%20of%20demonstrators%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20modern%20history.%20It%20is%20also%2C%20they%20say%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20visually%20documented%20atrocities%20in%20modern%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20anybody%20ever%20been%20held%20accountable%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Egyptian%20government%20previously%20called%20the%20human%20rights%20organisations%E2%80%99%20reports%20on%20the%20massacre%20%E2%80%9Cbiased%E2%80%9D.%20It%20has%20not%20responded%20to%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E%20questions%20about%20whether%20there%20was%20a%20need%20for%20further%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEgypt%20organised%20its%20own%20investigations%20into%20the%20massacre.%20One%20was%20by%20a%20fact-finding%20committee%20set%20up%C2%A0in%20late%202013%2C%20and%20another%20by%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20National%20Council%20for%20Human%20Rights.%20Both%20reviews%20said%20protesters%20at%20Rabaa%20were%20at%20fault%20because%20many%20were%20armed%2C%20something%20eyewitnesses%20still%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20conceded%20that%20security%20forces%20acted%20with%20excessive%20force%2C%20but%20did%20not%20recommend%20any%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20525px)%2085vw%2C%20525px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14162455%2FMohamed-Morsi.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22525%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14162455%2FMohamed-Morsi.jpg%20525w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14162455%2FMohamed-Morsi-234x300.jpg%20234w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668062%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22673%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIn%20July%202013%2C%20Egyptian%20President%20Mohamed%20Morsi%20was%20overthrown%20by%20a%20coalition%20comprising%20the%20military%2C%20opposition%20parties%20and%20religious%20figures%2C%20headed%20by%20current%20President%20Abdel%20Fattah%20el-Sisi.%20Photo%3B%20Wilson%20Dias%2FAgencia%20Brasil.%20CC%20BY%203.0%20br.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20Egypt%E2%80%99s%20parliament%20passed%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.loc.gov%2Fitem%2Fglobal-legal-monitor%2F2018-07-23%2Fegypt-bill-to-provide-judicial-immunity-to-military-commanders%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20a%20bill%20granting%20judicial%20immunity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20Bill%20granting%20judicial%20immunity%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20senior%20military%20leaders%20for%20acts%20they%20may%20have%20committed%20in%20the%20course%20of%20duty%2C%20from%20when%20the%20Egyptian%20constitution%20was%20suspended%20in%20July%202013%C2%A0to%20when%20parliament%20was%20reconvened%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%202021%2C%20Egypt%20approved%20amendments%20to%20laws%20governing%20its%20own%20Supreme%20Constitutional%20Court%20or%20SCC.%20These%20amendments%20mean%20that%20if%20any%20international%20court%20or%20tribunal%20should%20one%20day%20find%C2%A0Egypt%20guilty%20of%2C%20say%2C%20crimes%20against%20humanity%2C%20and%20orders%20reparations%2C%20the%20decision%20would%20be%20passed%20back%20to%20the%20SCC.%20This%20local%20court%20would%20then%20decide%20whether%20the%20verdict%20was%20valid%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%5BThe%20amendments%5D%20send%20a%20clear%20message%2C%E2%80%9D%20lawyer%20Mai%20El-Sadany%20wrote%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2Fsada%2F84941%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20a%202021%20post%20for%20Carnegie%20Endowment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202021%20post%20for%20Carnegie%20Endowment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20those%20inside%20the%20country%20%E2%80%A6%20%5Bthey%5D%20signal%20that%20those%20committing%20violations%20may%20continue%20to%20do%20so%20while%20enjoying%20protection%20domestically.%20To%20the%20global%20community%2C%20Egyptian%20authorities%20are%20challenging%20the%20international%20system.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeeking%20justice%20outside%20Egypt%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20search%20for%20justice%20has%20moved%20into%20the%20international%20arena%20for%20the%20past%20decade.%20But%20even%20then%2C%20there%20hasn%E2%80%99t%C2%A0been%20much%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHuman%20rights%20organisations%20have%20called%20on%20the%20United%20Nations%20Human%20Rights%20Committee%20to%20investigate%20the%20massacre%2C%20but%20it%20has%20so%20far%20chosen%20not%20to.%20Egypt%20has%20not%20fully%20acceded%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.african-court.org%2Fwpafc%2Fbasic-information%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20African%20Court%20on%20Human%20and%20Peoples'%20Rights%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAfrican%20Court%20on%20Human%20and%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Rights%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%C2%A0judicial%20arm%20of%20the%20African%20Union.%20Nor%20is%20it%20a%20member%20of%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20Egyptian%20lawyers%20and%20the%20Freedom%20and%20Justice%20Party%2C%20to%20which%20deposed%20President%20Morsi%20belongs%2C%20asked%20the%20ICC%20to%20investigate%20alleged%20crimes%20against%20humanity%20at%20Rabaa.%20But%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icc-cpi.int%2Fnews%2Fdetermination-office-prosecutor-communication-received-relation-egypt%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20ICC%20turned%20them%20down%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EICC%20turned%20them%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20that%20those%20requesting%20the%20investigation%20were%20not%20legitimate%20representatives%20of%20the%20Egyptian%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%C2%A0a%20senior%20Egyptian%20military%20commander%2C%20Mahmoud%20Hegazy%2C%20visited%20an%20arms%20trade%20fair%20in%20the%20UK%20in%202015%2C%20lawyers%20acting%20for%20the%20Freedom%20and%20Justice%20Party%20asked%20British%20police%20to%20arrest%20him%20over%20allegations%20of%20torture%20and%20because%20he%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2015%2Fnov%2F02%2Fegyptian-opposition-legal-battle-uk-immunity-sisi-aide%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22External%20link%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bintegral%20to%20the%20dispersal%20plans%20in%20Rabaa.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cintegral%20to%20the%20dispersal%20plans%20in%20Rabaa.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0The%C2%A0police%20turned%20down%20the%20request%20because%20Hegazy%20had%20special%20diplomatic%20immunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-is-reaching-out-to-egypt-but-there-are-challenges-in-the-offing%5C%22%3EIndia%20Is%20Reaching%20Out%20to%20Egypt%20%E2%80%93%20But%20There%20Are%20Challenges%20in%20the%20Offing%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20the%20only%20real%20options%20you%E2%80%99re%20left%20with%20are%20the%20sorts%20of%20inquiries%20by%20various%20United%20Nations%20bodies.%20Or%20universal%20jurisdiction%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Rupert%20Skilbeck%2C%20director%20of%20Redress%2C%20a%20London-based%20legal%20rights%20organisation%20that%20supports%20torture%20victims%20trying%20to%20obtain%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECould%20%E2%80%98universal%20jurisidiction%E2%80%99%20help%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20purest%20form%2C%20the%20legal%20principle%20of%20universal%20jurisdiction%20allows%20authorities%20in%20any%20country%20to%20prosecute%20individuals%20who%20have%20committed%20war%20crimes%20in%20any%20other%20country%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20they%20or%20their%20crimes%20have%20a%20connection%20to%20the%20prosecuting%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20practice%20however%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fsyrians-seek-justice-for-war-crimes-in-europes-courts%2Fa-55632079%5C%22%3Eit%20is%20often%20watered%20down%20by%20various%20considerations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20include%20whether%20there%20are%20witnesses%20in%20the%20prosecuting%20country%2C%20whether%20there%E2%80%99s%20any%20chance%20of%20arresting%20the%20alleged%20criminals%20and%20also%2C%20perhaps%20most%20importantly%2C%20whether%20local%20prosecutors%20want%20to%20take%20on%20the%20case.%20Often%20there%20are%20political%20aspects%20attached%20to%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20reality%20is%20that%20universal%20jurisdiction%20in%20this%20case%20would%20be%20quite%20difficult%2C%20because%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20real%20possibility%20of%20extraditing%20senior%20people%20from%20Egypt%2C%E2%80%9D%20Skilbeck%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20not%20many%20countries%20are%20prepared%20to%20do%20trials%20in%20absentia%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added%2C%20referring%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fegyptians-stand-trial-over-murder-of-italian-student-in-cairo%2Fa-59498732%5C%22%3Etrials%20conducted%20without%20a%20defendant%20in%20court%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20Germany%2C%20recently%20described%20as%20a%20world%20leader%20in%20its%20use%20of%20universal%20jurisdiction%2C%20a%20case%20against%20Egyptian%20officials%20is%20unlikely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%20of%20all%2C%20you%20would%20have%20to%20prove%20a%20crime%20against%20humanity%20had%20been%20committed%2C%20according%20to%20legal%20definitions%2C%20explained%20Andreas%20Sch%C3%BCller%2C%20director%20of%20the%20International%20Crimes%20and%20Accountability%20program%20at%20the%20Berlin-based%20European%20Center%20for%20Constitutional%20and%20Human%20Rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20organisation%20was%20a%20prime%20mover%20behind%20Germany%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgerman-court-finds-syrian-ex-colonel-guilty-of-crimes-against-humanity%2Fa-60407021%5C%22%3Erecent%20prosecution%20of%20Syrian%20war%20criminals%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0using%20universal%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20far%20as%20I%20know%20there%20are%20no%20courts%20or%20other%20institutions%20that%20have%20made%20this%20finding.%20So%20you%E2%80%99d%20need%20to%20establish%20it%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20which%20requires%20a%20big%20effort%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sch%C3%BCller%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22How%20to%20Indict%20Perpetrators%20%E2%80%93%20Nuremberg%E2%80%99s%20History%20Lessons%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fhow-to-indict-persecutors%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20Indict%20Perpetrators%20%E2%80%93%20Nuremberg%E2%80%99s%20History%20Lessons%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20against%20Syrian%20war%20criminals%20went%20ahead%20because%20of%20a%20confluence%20of%20factors%2C%20including%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgerman-torture-trial-a-syrian-opposition-legend-speaks-out%2Fa-54727286%5C%22%3Ewitnesses%2C%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0perpetrators%20in%20Germany%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20political%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20this%20is%20not%20like%20the%20Syrian%20case%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Sch%C3%BCller.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20no%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20the%20Syrian%20government.%20Egypt%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20political%20support%20internationally.%20It%20is%20also%20not%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20relevant%20UN%20treaties%20or%20the%20ICC%E2%80%99s%20Rome%20Statute.%20So%20nobody%20is%20really%20willing%20to%20take%20these%20cases%2C%20which%20would%20also%20require%20a%20very%20targeted%20investigation%20and%20a%20certain%20constellation%20of%20factors%20to%20get%20it%20prosecuted.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20see%20this%20all%20the%20time%20in%20human%20rights%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20Redress%E2%80%99%20Skilbeck%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhere%20certain%20Western%20countries%20will%20not%20take%20a%20firm%20stance%20against%20other%20countries%20because%20of%20the%20political%20situation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESch%C3%BCller%20also%20believes%20international%20interest%20has%20shifted%20to%20countries%20like%20Ukraine%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fsudan-over-3-million-displaced-by-conflict-un-says%2Fa-66201174%5C%22%3ESudan%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0or%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAmr%20Magdi%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20at%20Human%20Rights%20Watch%2C%20has%20similar%20opinions.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20political%20climate%20in%20the%20region%20has%20contributed%20to%20human%20rights%20violations%20in%20Egypt%20being%20overlooked%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CAt%20that%20time%2C%20the%20whole%20region%20was%20rife%20with%20problems%2C%20including%20civil%20war%20in%20Syria%2C%20Yemen%20and%20Libya.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Egyptian%20government%20has%20managed%20to%20play%20on%20issues%20that%20concern%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%20Magdi%20argued%2C%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cso%20that%20democracy%20and%20human%20rights%20are%20overlooked%20in%20exchange%20for%20Egypt%20taking%20care%20of%20European%20interests%2C%20such%20as%20combating%20irregular%20migration%2C%20security%20cooperation%20and%20economic%20relations.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanges%20in%20attitudes%20toward%C2%A0Egypt%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20there%20may%20yet%20be%20some%20minimal%20hope%20that%20justice%20could%20one%20day%20be%20brought%20to%20bear%20on%20the%20Rabaa%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20legal%20decisions%20made%20about%20the%20case%20happened%20in%20the%20immediate%20aftermath%20of%20the%202013%20military%20coup.%20Back%20then%2C%20the%20international%20community%20appeared%20to%20be%20uncertain%20how%20the%20Egyptian%20government%20would%20develop%20%E2%80%93%20the%20military%20coup%20also%20had%20many%20supporters%20and%20the%20Morsi%20government%20had%20faced%20popular%20protests%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20that%20has%20changed%20and%20the%20current%20government%2C%20led%20by%C2%A0Abdel%20Fattah%20el-Sissi%2C%20is%20more%20often%20criticised%20for%20its%20authoritarianism%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Flgbtq-rights-in-egypt-queer-community-battles-crackdown%2Fa-65170739%5C%22%3Ean%20increasingly%20dire%20human%20rights%20record%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20point%20is%20a%20good%20one%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%C2%A0Skilbeck.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20litigation%20was%20done%20very%20quickly%20after%20the%20events.%20While%20things%20are%20hot%2C%20people%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20act%C2%A0immediately.%20In%20any%20event%2C%20it%20often%20takes%20quite%20a%20long%20time%20to%20bring%20evidence%20together.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%C2%A0to%20long-running%20historical%20examples%2C%20like%20international%20tribunals%20looking%20at%20crimes%20in%20Rwanda%2C%20Cambodia%2C%20the%20former%20Yugoslavia%2C%20as%20well%20as%20World%20War%20II%2C%20noting%C2%A0that%2C%20%E2%80%9Cinternational%20justice%20normally%20does%20take%20a%20very%20long%20time.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20a%20normal%20trial%20for%20murder%20will%20probably%20take%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20to%20be%20completed%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CSo%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20surprising%20they%20take%20so%20long.%20But%C2%A0the%20long-sighted%20approach%20is%20absolutely%20the%20only%20way%20to%20do%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fegypts-rabaa-massacre-still-waiting-for-justice%2Fa-66504869%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692011139000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14161516%2FRabaa-Square-being-cleared.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhy-egypts-rabaa-massacre-didnt-go-to-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20massacres%20of%20protesters%20in%20modern%20history%20%E2%80%93%20and%20also%20one%20of%20the%20best%20documented.%20So%20why%20is%20nobody%20using%20the%20plentiful%20evidence%20available%20to%20bring%20Egyptian%20security%20forces%20to%20justice%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhy-egypts-rabaa-massacre-didnt-go-to-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Woman%20who%20cooked%20poisonous%20beef%20wellington%20details%20what%20happened%20in%20written%20statement%20to%20police%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692011100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F70x70%2Fskynews-erin-patterson-mushroom_6246348.jpg%3F20230810131446%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwoman-who-cooked-deadly-mushroom-lunch-says-she-ended-up-in-hospital-herself-after-meal-12939883%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20woman%20who%20cooked%20a%20lunch%20that%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20left%20three%20people%20dead%20and%20one%20fighting%20for%20his%20life%20from%20a%20suspected%20mushroom%